1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:03,702
(After a turbulent night)

2
00:00:03,703 --> 00:00:06,272
(The morning of Day 6)

3
00:00:06,707 --> 00:00:09,075
I was really curious
because you looked so happy...

4
00:00:09,309 --> 00:00:11,443
when you came back last night.

5
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:13,479
I hit on Jung Won so hard yesterday.

6
00:00:14,815 --> 00:00:17,116
And that's why my pride got hurt so much.

7
00:00:17,785 --> 00:00:19,652
You really like Jung Won, don't you?

8
00:00:20,487 --> 00:00:22,755
Last night, you said, "I like him so much.
What should I do?"

9
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:25,024
Everyone knows that.

10
00:00:25,759 --> 00:00:29,328
(Jin Young came back to the room
after her talk with Jung Won last night.)

11
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:30,830
- I'm having fun.
- How adorable.

12
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:31,864
Things must be going well.

13
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:33,165
- The talk must have gone well.
- Seriously

14
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,802
I know. I like him so much.
What should I do?

15
00:00:35,803 --> 00:00:36,969
I like him. What should I do?

16
00:00:37,551 --> 00:00:39,138
- What should I do?
- That much?

17
00:00:39,139 --> 00:00:40,139
She must have really liked it.

18
00:00:40,908 --> 00:00:43,142
I was obsessed with him yesterday.

19
00:00:43,887 --> 00:00:46,688
I kept asking where Jung Won was, and...

20
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:50,816
Because he was talking to Ji Hye?

21
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:52,585
It's so stressful.

22
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,457
(Ji Hye comes into the powder room.)

23
00:00:57,458 --> 00:00:58,657
They're staying in the same room.

24
00:00:59,493 --> 00:01:00,892
(Glancing)

25
00:01:00,893 --> 00:01:02,395
Oh, my gosh.

26
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:14,573
(Jin Young and Ji Hye do their makeup
without talking.)

27
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,875
It's so intense
between Jin Young and Ji Hye.

28
00:01:23,183 --> 00:01:25,451
"Today is the day-drinking date,
a chance for everyone to have..."

29
00:01:25,452 --> 00:01:26,619
"bold and honest conversations."

30
00:01:27,972 --> 00:01:30,623
A day-drinking date? It's meant
to push things ahead, isn't it?

31
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:33,259
(A day-drinking date determined
by the older women's choices)

32
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,060
Hey.

33
00:01:34,862 --> 00:01:35,895
We need to send it.

34
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:37,196
What?

35
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:40,700
The name of the younger man. Come on.

36
00:01:40,968 --> 00:01:41,801
Okay.

37
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:45,938
What is Yu Jin doing?

38
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,840
Yu Jin.

39
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:48,941
I said we need to do this.

40
00:01:49,243 --> 00:01:50,976
- I already did.
- Did you? Okay.

41
00:01:51,946 --> 00:01:53,079
I didn't know because I couldn't see you.

42
00:01:55,749 --> 00:01:59,251
Actually, if I said I was totally fine,

43
00:01:59,387 --> 00:02:01,821
that would be a lie.

44
00:02:01,989 --> 00:02:05,024
I couldn't look into her eyes.
I don't know why.

45
00:02:05,025 --> 00:02:07,459
I became really guilty for no reason.

46
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:11,998
Oh, no.

47
00:02:11,999 --> 00:02:13,525
(Yu Jin and Ji Seung both have feelings
for Si Won.)

48
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:15,801
Maybe she feels guilty about it now.

49
00:02:16,504 --> 00:02:19,138
Because she realized how much stronger
her feelings for Si Won have become.

50
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:19,905
It's weighing on her.

51
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:21,808
But it's not like she broke up a couple.

52
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:22,742
Still.

53
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:24,643
- Still?
- Still, she feels bad for her.

54
00:02:25,345 --> 00:02:28,314
(Ji Seung sends the name of her choice.)

55
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:31,350
I really thought hard about it.

56
00:02:31,351 --> 00:02:35,588
Now that my roommate is
also involved in this...

57
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:39,258
because she has feelings for him too,

58
00:02:39,259 --> 00:02:41,760
that made me hesitate a little.

59
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,332
She should just focus on herself.

60
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:49,835
(She sends the name after much thought.)

61
00:02:50,237 --> 00:02:51,238
(While the women are choosing...)

62
00:02:51,239 --> 00:02:52,839
(Yeon House)

63
00:02:54,241 --> 00:02:58,044
So you're going out with Ji Hye
no matter what today?

64
00:02:58,045 --> 00:02:58,978
Yes.

65
00:03:03,785 --> 00:03:05,077
(Ji Hye's interest
in Jung Won bothers him.)

66
00:03:05,078 --> 00:03:06,753
The two of them just happened to be there?

67
00:03:06,754 --> 00:03:09,322
You're not asking Jin Young out?

68
00:03:09,957 --> 00:03:12,658
So once it's over, you never look back?

69
00:03:12,659 --> 00:03:14,593
Never. I'm done with everyone
except Ji Hye now.

70
00:03:14,594 --> 00:03:15,728
- Really?
- Yes.

71
00:03:19,499 --> 00:03:20,766
(He openly shows
how he feels about Ji Hye.)

72
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,000
I think he really made up his mind now.

73
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:24,737
Jin Woo. I'm really curious about him.

74
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:28,574
(Jin Woo happens
to enter the common area.)

75
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:31,444
(Glancing)

76
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:32,512
(Passing by)

77
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:35,681
(Jin Woo passes by Jung Won.)

78
00:03:40,954 --> 00:03:42,388
(Glancing)

79
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,601
(Glancing)

80
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,529
Gosh.

81
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:52,705
What's wrong?
Did you drink a lot last night?

82
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,968
- Because of you.
- Sorry?

83
00:03:54,969 --> 00:03:55,834
Because of you.

84
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:57,269
Why is it because of me?

85
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:00,059
He told him straight up.

86
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,306
(Jung Won and Jin Young's closeness
bothers him.)

87
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:06,245
(Jung Won is now on everyone's radar.)

88
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,447
- Don't tell me that's Jin Woo again.
- Jin Woo.

89
00:04:08,949 --> 00:04:09,815
Is he doing the dishes?

90
00:04:09,983 --> 00:04:11,010
- Ju Hee is there.
- That's Ju Hee.

91
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,187
Hello.

92
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:16,855
Good morning.

93
00:04:17,824 --> 00:04:19,057
- Hello.
- Hi.

94
00:04:20,027 --> 00:04:20,860
I just...

95
00:04:20,861 --> 00:04:22,395
(Staring)

96
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:24,497
(Yun So tries to read Ju Hee's face.)

97
00:04:25,899 --> 00:04:31,071
(Ju Hee and Yun So's talk last night)

98
00:04:31,203 --> 00:04:33,272
So have you more or less
made up your mind?

99
00:04:33,573 --> 00:04:34,740
About the Final Selection.

100
00:04:35,242 --> 00:04:37,643
I'm not asking you to tell me your choice.
I just want to know if you have.

101
00:04:38,479 --> 00:04:40,546
I'll tell you tomorrow.

102
00:04:41,548 --> 00:04:43,649
Then promise me you'll tell me tomorrow.

103
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:45,317
I'm not going to ask you anymore.

104
00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:46,585
Okay?

105
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:50,322
He's so serious.

106
00:04:50,324 --> 00:04:52,258
(He didn't get the answer he wanted
from Ju Hee.)

107
00:04:53,193 --> 00:04:55,393
(His eyes keep drifting toward Ju Hee,)

108
00:04:55,394 --> 00:04:57,630
(even during breakfast.)

109
00:04:58,365 --> 00:04:59,098
(Reading the room)

110
00:04:59,099 --> 00:04:59,932
She's reading the room.

111
00:05:01,868 --> 00:05:03,535
(Approaching)

112
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:06,839
Did you eat something?

113
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:08,908
- I did.
- Did you eat a bagel?

114
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:09,809
Yes.

115
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:11,844
I'm going to lie down in my room.

116
00:05:12,379 --> 00:05:14,413
Yes. Go and get some rest.

117
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:15,581
(Ju Hee leaves without saying much.)

118
00:05:15,716 --> 00:05:16,582
See you later.

119
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:18,684
See you.

120
00:05:20,387 --> 00:05:22,822
Since I'm the one waiting,

121
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:25,357
I can't help but feel a little scared.

122
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,627
I think we need to talk.

123
00:05:29,362 --> 00:05:33,465
I hope the conversation can soothe
my feelings a little.

124
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:38,671
(Yun So wants answers from Ju Hee.)

125
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:42,541
(Jin Woo leaves the common area first.)

126
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:45,978
(While Si Won and Yun So are
cleaning up...)

127
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:50,516
(Ji Seung comes to the common area.)

128
00:05:51,151 --> 00:05:52,685
- Hi.
- Good morning.

129
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,787
- Hi.
- Good morning.

130
00:05:55,055 --> 00:05:57,156
Why are you all dressed up today?

131
00:05:57,324 --> 00:05:58,224
Come on.

132
00:05:58,758 --> 00:05:59,825
Did you eat something?

133
00:06:00,627 --> 00:06:01,493
Aren't you hungry?

134
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,228
Maybe I should eat something.

135
00:06:03,463 --> 00:06:04,730
Have some cereal.

136
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:05,898
- Cereal?
- We have milk too.

137
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:07,166
Maybe I should.

138
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,201
- Yes.
- You can eat that.

139
00:06:10,437 --> 00:06:13,405
Si Won doesn't look happy to see her now.

140
00:06:13,406 --> 00:06:15,841
Si Won, are you going
somewhere nice today?

141
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,443
Yes, I'm going somewhere fancy.

142
00:06:18,446 --> 00:06:19,479
He's lukewarm.

143
00:06:20,947 --> 00:06:22,615
(Glancing)

144
00:06:24,751 --> 00:06:26,519
Enjoy your breakfast.

145
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,087
- Enjoy.
- Okay.

146
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:30,222
(Without any particular interaction
with Ji Seung, Si Won leaves.)

147
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:31,624
I should take this with me.

148
00:06:32,993 --> 00:06:33,893
I'll take this to my room.

149
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:37,563
The atmosphere has changed a lot.

150
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:45,472
(Ji Seung leaves the empty common area.)

151
00:06:45,473 --> 00:06:47,039
Oh, no.

152
00:06:49,342 --> 00:06:52,044
(She goes back to her room.)

153
00:06:54,715 --> 00:06:57,516
What's worse is they're roommates.

154
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,151
Have you made up your mind, even a little?

155
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:02,821
My mind? I think it's becoming
clearer for me.

156
00:07:04,692 --> 00:07:07,793
They feel very young
once I found out their ages.

157
00:07:08,061 --> 00:07:09,094
To be honest,

158
00:07:09,672 --> 00:07:13,875
I don't feel the age difference
when I'm with Si Won.

159
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,901
You don't feel that at all?

160
00:07:16,103 --> 00:07:18,003
Don't you feel it
at least once in a while?

161
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:23,108
From time to time,
because of external factors, I do feel it.

162
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,443
But in general, I don't.

163
00:07:25,011 --> 00:07:28,280
He's really stable.

164
00:07:29,349 --> 00:07:30,917
"No, I don't feel that."

165
00:07:30,918 --> 00:07:32,251
That's what she's saying.

166
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,387
She's saying, "He's super stable."

167
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:36,322
Goodness.

168
00:07:36,323 --> 00:07:38,691
I don't know how it'll end,

169
00:07:39,192 --> 00:07:41,560
but I'm thinking about what will happen
once we're out of here.

170
00:07:42,495 --> 00:07:46,631
(A subtle tension continues
between Yu Jin and Ji Seung.)

171
00:07:51,071 --> 00:07:51,751
Yes?

172
00:07:51,752 --> 00:07:53,344
(Jung Won pays a visit
to Ji Hye and Jin Young's room.)

173
00:07:53,345 --> 00:07:54,540
That's Ji Hye and Jin Young's room.

174
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:55,641
Hi.

175
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:57,710
- What is it?
- I'm here because I was bored.

176
00:07:57,944 --> 00:07:59,411
- Bored?
- Do you want to take a walk?

177
00:07:59,412 --> 00:08:01,780
- Sure.
- Okay. I'll be back in a minute.

178
00:08:02,282 --> 00:08:05,351
(Jung Won goes out
for a walk with Jin Young.)

179
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:10,222
(Slipping out)

180
00:08:11,725 --> 00:08:12,658
Are you going out?

181
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:16,695
(Turning around)

182
00:08:16,696 --> 00:08:17,562
She's not answering.

183
00:08:18,898 --> 00:08:22,200
(Jin Young leaves the room
without answering.)

184
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:27,406
What were you doing?

185
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:29,175
- I was lying down.
- Really?

186
00:08:29,176 --> 00:08:30,309
I was sleeping.

187
00:08:31,144 --> 00:08:33,011
- You look really great today.
- Do I?

188
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:34,513
- Yes.
- Are you falling for me?

189
00:08:35,148 --> 00:08:36,615
It's not that serious.

190
00:08:37,384 --> 00:08:39,785
(Sighing)

191
00:08:39,786 --> 00:08:42,555
I want to get driven around
by a man today.

192
00:08:42,656 --> 00:08:45,491
If there's a chance,
please ride with me today.

193
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,726
Just run over and hop in?

194
00:08:47,894 --> 00:08:49,595
Yes. Just run and grab the chance.

195
00:08:49,596 --> 00:08:51,363
Grab the chance to be with you?

196
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:53,031
(Come and grab me!)

197
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,333
"Grab the chance to be with me."

198
00:08:54,334 --> 00:08:55,901
- Jung Won never changes, does he?
- That's hilarious.

199
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:57,069
Since Day One.

200
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:58,906
That's what makes Jung Won so attractive.

201
00:08:58,907 --> 00:09:00,172
That's his personality.

202
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,741
Now, you should grab the chance
to be with me.

203
00:09:02,742 --> 00:09:04,243
It's time for you to grab it.

204
00:09:04,778 --> 00:09:08,214
I've been trying too hard so far.

205
00:09:08,215 --> 00:09:09,782
Have you? I think you should try harder.

206
00:09:09,783 --> 00:09:11,050
- Harder than this?
- Yes.

207
00:09:11,184 --> 00:09:13,352
I should try harder to be with you?

208
00:09:13,353 --> 00:09:14,486
No, that's not what I'm saying.

209
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:16,889
I'll go inside.

210
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,792
The conversation didn't go anywhere.

211
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:21,126
(A conversation that didn't get anywhere)

212
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:26,565
Actually, I went there to see Ji Hye.

213
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:27,866
Oh, really?

214
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,069
I've already talked with Jin Young a lot,

215
00:09:30,436 --> 00:09:33,072
so I went there to talk more with Ji Hye,

216
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,775
but Jin Young came out.

217
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:38,210
When Jin Young asked me,

218
00:09:38,545 --> 00:09:41,247
"Do you want to talk?"

219
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:42,781
I couldn't tell her...

220
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,951
that I was there to talk to someone else.

221
00:09:46,353 --> 00:09:47,787
So I ended up talking
to Jin Young instead.

222
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:49,988
I was very confused.

223
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,725
(To whom is Jung Won's heart
heading toward?)

224
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:58,030
Jung Won knows
Jin Young likes him very much.

225
00:09:58,164 --> 00:10:00,766
- Right.
- Does knowing make you lose interest?

226
00:10:01,735 --> 00:10:03,701
Everyone has their own pace
when it comes to love.

227
00:10:03,702 --> 00:10:05,534
The pace at which feelings grow.

228
00:10:05,535 --> 00:10:08,601
If I was taking things at 40,

229
00:10:08,602 --> 00:10:10,502
and she came at 80,

230
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:13,201
that would put a lot of pressure on me.

231
00:10:13,202 --> 00:10:14,202
Right.

232
00:10:15,542 --> 00:10:16,509
I got a text message.

233
00:10:18,309 --> 00:10:21,809
(Only the younger men receive a text.)

234
00:10:22,044 --> 00:10:23,975
It says, "Check who your date is."

235
00:10:24,709 --> 00:10:26,541
You could've been chosen or not.

236
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:28,509
I might not have been anyone's choice.

237
00:10:30,042 --> 00:10:31,908
Who did they want to go
on a day-drinking date with?

238
00:10:31,909 --> 00:10:33,242
(Who did the women choose as their date?)

239
00:10:38,909 --> 00:10:42,141
(Si Won goes to the QR Room
to see who his date is.)

240
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:43,909
Who do you think chose Si Won?

241
00:10:48,809 --> 00:10:50,742
Si Won must have gotten two votes.

242
00:10:56,009 --> 00:10:59,774
(The older women who asked Si Won out)

243
00:10:59,775 --> 00:11:01,574
(Two people)

244
00:11:01,575 --> 00:11:02,642
As we expected.

245
00:11:06,809 --> 00:11:07,875
Gosh.

246
00:11:09,109 --> 00:11:10,974
(Si Won got two votes,
but he seems frustrated.)

247
00:11:10,975 --> 00:11:12,242
It must be hard.

248
00:11:13,009 --> 00:11:16,108
If it were the beginning,
I'd be happy about two votes.

249
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:20,075
I've somewhat made up my mind now.

250
00:11:21,109 --> 00:11:24,575
So I'm worried about going on dates
with two people.

251
00:11:25,009 --> 00:11:27,474
I kind of had a feeling who they would be,

252
00:11:27,475 --> 00:11:28,542
so that made me more anxious.

253
00:11:29,675 --> 00:11:33,774
(The second younger man)

254
00:11:33,775 --> 00:11:36,409
(Yun So)

255
00:11:37,242 --> 00:11:39,775
I hope there are no more surprises.

256
00:11:43,491 --> 00:11:44,574
(You have one day-drinking date.)

257
00:11:44,575 --> 00:11:46,374
One person. There you go.

258
00:11:46,375 --> 00:11:47,841
I'm glad.

259
00:11:47,842 --> 00:11:49,042
(Nodding)

260
00:11:50,342 --> 00:11:54,209
(Will Yun So go on a date with Ju Hee?)

261
00:11:55,509 --> 00:11:59,942
(The third younger man, Jin Woo)

262
00:12:00,209 --> 00:12:02,609
I got to talk to Jin Young yesterday,

263
00:12:03,042 --> 00:12:04,809
the person I was into.

264
00:12:06,409 --> 00:12:09,541
I hope she asks me out...

265
00:12:09,542 --> 00:12:11,209
if she sees me romantically.

266
00:12:13,175 --> 00:12:16,408
(Who asked Jin Woo out?)

267
00:12:16,409 --> 00:12:18,041
(You were not chosen
for a day-drinking date.)

268
00:12:18,042 --> 00:12:19,542
Oh, my.

269
00:12:20,342 --> 00:12:22,908
That sound effect doesn't
play there, right?

270
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:23,808
Come on.

271
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:25,975
- They wouldn't do that.
- If I heard that,

272
00:12:26,275 --> 00:12:27,709
I would want to throw my phone.

273
00:12:31,509 --> 00:12:36,009
(Jin Woo will stay at Yeon House
without a date.)

274
00:12:37,342 --> 00:12:40,309
(The fourth younger man, Jun Han)

275
00:12:41,542 --> 00:12:43,442
I talked to Ji Hye.

276
00:12:43,742 --> 00:12:45,808
Since I'm into her,

277
00:12:45,809 --> 00:12:49,509
I asked her to give me a chance
to show off my charm like Jung Won.

278
00:12:50,402 --> 00:12:53,502
I told her that we should go on a date.

279
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:57,009
I wanted to go on a date with Ji Hye.

280
00:12:58,542 --> 00:13:00,909
Did Ji Hye choose him?

281
00:13:04,609 --> 00:13:05,809
My date...

282
00:13:09,242 --> 00:13:10,541
Let's see.

283
00:13:10,542 --> 00:13:12,975
(Curious)

284
00:13:16,009 --> 00:13:17,209
(You were not chosen for a date.)

285
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:18,375
He doesn't have a date.

286
00:13:20,575 --> 00:13:21,775
That's sad.

287
00:13:24,175 --> 00:13:28,509
(Jun Han didn't get chosen
by any of the older women.)

288
00:13:29,675 --> 00:13:33,009
(The last younger man, Jung Won)

289
00:13:34,442 --> 00:13:36,675
That means the rest of them chose him.

290
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:38,774
(You have two day-drinking dates.)

291
00:13:38,775 --> 00:13:39,809
That's complicated.

292
00:13:41,409 --> 00:13:42,641
(Uneasy)

293
00:13:42,642 --> 00:13:45,208
(Jung Won's expression turns serious
after seeing the results.)

294
00:13:45,209 --> 00:13:46,775
He seems to have mixed feelings.

295
00:13:47,909 --> 00:13:51,909
(Will these dates help
Jung Won make up his mind?)

296
00:13:52,142 --> 00:13:54,209
These dates today will be very important.

297
00:13:54,809 --> 00:13:55,675
Right.

298
00:13:56,909 --> 00:14:00,642
(The older women are waiting
for the younger men.)

299
00:14:01,975 --> 00:14:07,609
(Which younger man does each woman want
to go on a day-drinking date with?)

300
00:14:08,475 --> 00:14:11,342
(The older women's choice,
the first day-drinking date)

301
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:19,074
(The first older woman
to meet a younger man)

302
00:14:19,075 --> 00:14:22,042
(Jin Young)

303
00:14:23,075 --> 00:14:27,808
(Who did she ask out
on a day-drinking date?)

304
00:14:27,809 --> 00:14:29,109
(Smiling)

305
00:14:31,975 --> 00:14:32,908
As I expected.

306
00:14:32,909 --> 00:14:34,108
(Jung Won)

307
00:14:34,109 --> 00:14:34,975
I knew it.

308
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:36,709
(Smiling brightly)

309
00:14:36,942 --> 00:14:37,809
As I expected.

310
00:14:38,609 --> 00:14:39,875
- You did?
- Yes.

311
00:14:42,775 --> 00:14:43,842
Isn't this water?

312
00:14:44,942 --> 00:14:48,208
- It's alcohol. We'll be day drinking.
- Day drinking?

313
00:14:48,209 --> 00:14:49,342
- Yes.
- This must be a drinking glass.

314
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:52,474
(Shy)

315
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:54,242
- You don't mind drinking?
- No, I don't.

316
00:14:55,275 --> 00:14:56,775
- Shall we touch glasses?
- Yes.

317
00:14:59,675 --> 00:15:03,809
(Will alcohol help them open up
and express their true feelings?)

318
00:15:04,675 --> 00:15:06,475
It's not wrapped well.

319
00:15:08,542 --> 00:15:09,342
Try it.

320
00:15:10,675 --> 00:15:11,975
It's sloppy, but try it.

321
00:15:13,742 --> 00:15:14,642
(Humming)

322
00:15:15,042 --> 00:15:16,674
It's so good wrapped in seaweed.

323
00:15:16,675 --> 00:15:17,509
It's good.

324
00:15:17,909 --> 00:15:19,242
It's delicious.

325
00:15:19,409 --> 00:15:20,653
Wow.

326
00:15:21,626 --> 00:15:22,742
This is really good.

327
00:15:23,875 --> 00:15:27,475
I feel like you'll spend some time
with me and leave.

328
00:15:30,209 --> 00:15:32,774
- There are so many surprises, right?
- I have no choice.

329
00:15:32,775 --> 00:15:34,374
I should make you drink a lot...

330
00:15:34,375 --> 00:15:35,641
so you can't go anywhere.

331
00:15:35,642 --> 00:15:37,875
She really likes him.

332
00:15:39,242 --> 00:15:41,342
- I heard everything.
- About what?

333
00:15:41,642 --> 00:15:45,641
You had so much fun with Ji Hye
at the amusement park.

334
00:15:45,642 --> 00:15:46,741
I heard it all.

335
00:15:46,742 --> 00:15:47,641
Who told you?

336
00:15:47,642 --> 00:15:49,409
I have my way.

337
00:15:50,009 --> 00:15:53,109
It seems like the women chat a lot.

338
00:15:54,642 --> 00:15:58,608
You know Ji Hye and I are roommates.

339
00:15:58,609 --> 00:16:01,308
We rarely talk about men.

340
00:16:01,309 --> 00:16:02,808
- Really?
- Seriously.

341
00:16:02,809 --> 00:16:05,341
We don't talk about who we're into...

342
00:16:05,342 --> 00:16:06,441
or anything like that.

343
00:16:06,442 --> 00:16:07,608
Why not?

344
00:16:07,609 --> 00:16:09,309
Usually, women talk a lot about that.

345
00:16:09,975 --> 00:16:10,809
I think...

346
00:16:12,075 --> 00:16:16,342
we just avoid it so we don't
make each other uncomfortable.

347
00:16:19,175 --> 00:16:21,075
So if you don't tell me, I wouldn't know.

348
00:16:22,309 --> 00:16:23,609
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

349
00:16:26,109 --> 00:16:26,909
Well...

350
00:16:28,309 --> 00:16:30,308
I just laughed a lot
at the amusement park.

351
00:16:30,309 --> 00:16:31,642
- Do you want some soup?
- No.

352
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:33,775
I don't get jealous.

353
00:16:34,075 --> 00:16:35,909
- You don't?
- I'm not the jealous type.

354
00:16:37,609 --> 00:16:38,774
Sounds like you are.

355
00:16:38,775 --> 00:16:39,575
What?

356
00:16:40,042 --> 00:16:43,541
(He doesn't give a clear answer
about Ji Hye.)

357
00:16:43,542 --> 00:16:45,741
Why did you come to our room this morning?

358
00:16:45,742 --> 00:16:47,642
- What?
- Why did you come to find me?

359
00:16:48,409 --> 00:16:49,242
I was bored.

360
00:16:50,042 --> 00:16:50,909
Did you miss me?

361
00:16:51,575 --> 00:16:52,342
Yes.

362
00:16:55,309 --> 00:16:56,609
- Is that so?
- And you came out.

363
00:16:57,975 --> 00:16:58,842
So...

364
00:17:00,009 --> 00:17:01,509
I just went to hang out.

365
00:17:02,442 --> 00:17:03,709
He's lying, right?

366
00:17:04,675 --> 00:17:05,774
You were in there.

367
00:17:05,775 --> 00:17:09,608
I'm a little annoyed
by how nonchalant you are.

368
00:17:09,609 --> 00:17:12,074
- What are you talking about?
- It annoys me.

369
00:17:12,075 --> 00:17:13,841
I said, "Did you miss me?"

370
00:17:13,842 --> 00:17:17,175
And you didn't get shy
when you were answering that.

371
00:17:17,442 --> 00:17:18,708
Well, I missed you.

372
00:17:18,709 --> 00:17:19,808
What else can I say?

373
00:17:19,809 --> 00:17:21,108
The answer was yes, so I said yes.

374
00:17:21,109 --> 00:17:22,408
You don't get shy.

375
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:24,408
You're just always so confident.

376
00:17:24,409 --> 00:17:26,408
- That's not true.
- Confident and relaxed.

377
00:17:26,409 --> 00:17:27,708
Not at all.

378
00:17:27,709 --> 00:17:29,908
With the other guys, I can tell.

379
00:17:29,909 --> 00:17:32,608
I can tell how they feel...

380
00:17:32,609 --> 00:17:34,509
and what they're thinking.

381
00:17:35,009 --> 00:17:37,942
"He's really nervous around me."

382
00:17:38,609 --> 00:17:39,374
But with you,

383
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:41,409
I can't read you at all.

384
00:17:41,709 --> 00:17:44,509
It's like...

385
00:17:47,475 --> 00:17:48,441
What do you mean?

386
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:52,174
You're always so composed.

387
00:17:52,175 --> 00:17:53,674
I'm not trying to hide my feelings.

388
00:17:53,675 --> 00:17:54,875
This is just who I am.

389
00:17:55,809 --> 00:17:58,209
(Tilting her head)

390
00:18:00,009 --> 00:18:03,809
Do you want me to be nervous?

391
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,442
It's not...

392
00:18:06,909 --> 00:18:09,074
that I want you to be a certain way.

393
00:18:09,075 --> 00:18:12,008
I can't really tell what you're thinking,

394
00:18:12,009 --> 00:18:13,042
so it's frustrating.

395
00:18:14,175 --> 00:18:15,175
What I'm thinking.

396
00:18:16,542 --> 00:18:17,975
You're...

397
00:18:19,075 --> 00:18:20,509
so hard to read.

398
00:18:21,609 --> 00:18:22,409
I have no idea.

399
00:18:23,509 --> 00:18:26,174
She can't read him...

400
00:18:26,175 --> 00:18:28,742
because he has good control
of his emotions.

401
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:31,175
I understand why it's confusing.

402
00:18:32,675 --> 00:18:34,675
You don't really talk about yourself.

403
00:18:35,309 --> 00:18:36,174
To whom?

404
00:18:36,175 --> 00:18:37,274
To me.

405
00:18:37,275 --> 00:18:39,942
I still don't know what you're like.

406
00:18:40,575 --> 00:18:42,241
- Are you confused?
- No.

407
00:18:42,242 --> 00:18:44,341
I can tell you're into me,

408
00:18:44,342 --> 00:18:46,274
but I can't really figure you out.

409
00:18:46,275 --> 00:18:48,408
Like the real you is hidden.

410
00:18:48,409 --> 00:18:49,775
- The real me?
- Yes.

411
00:18:51,442 --> 00:18:53,009
- Are you curious?
- Yes.

412
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:55,409
You don't tell me.

413
00:18:56,275 --> 00:18:57,941
What should I say about myself?

414
00:18:57,942 --> 00:18:59,874
- What do you want me to say?
- You have a lot of secrets.

415
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:01,109
Should I say I'm a good person?

416
00:19:01,775 --> 00:19:03,309
- I'm a good person.
- You're so secretive.

417
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,242
Do you have any questions for me?

418
00:19:08,509 --> 00:19:09,374
Questions?

419
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:11,442
Tell me what you want to know about me.

420
00:19:11,875 --> 00:19:13,375
- Specifically?
- Yes.

421
00:19:16,909 --> 00:19:18,808
- Who are you most comfortable with...
- What?

422
00:19:18,809 --> 00:19:19,709
among the girls?

423
00:19:20,142 --> 00:19:21,541
- Comfortable?
- Not the person you're into.

424
00:19:21,542 --> 00:19:22,974
Who do you feel most relaxed...

425
00:19:22,975 --> 00:19:23,774
when talking to them?

426
00:19:23,775 --> 00:19:25,675
Who do I feel most comfortable talking to?

427
00:19:29,242 --> 00:19:30,908
The person I feel most comfortable with...

428
00:19:30,909 --> 00:19:32,375
would be Ji Hye.

429
00:19:35,442 --> 00:19:37,308
I just feel relaxed when I talk to her.

430
00:19:37,309 --> 00:19:39,309
(He feels relaxed when he's with Ji Hye.)

431
00:19:39,475 --> 00:19:41,209
You two seem to hit it off.

432
00:19:41,609 --> 00:19:44,975
Just making eye contact
with her makes me laugh.

433
00:19:45,442 --> 00:19:46,375
Goodness.

434
00:19:46,975 --> 00:19:48,309
I feel that comfortable with her.

435
00:19:50,642 --> 00:19:54,642
(Jung Won's answer gives Jin Young
a lot to think about.)

436
00:19:54,809 --> 00:19:58,409
But when I'm with you,

437
00:19:58,976 --> 00:20:00,977
I feel like there's
a certain level of tension between us...

438
00:20:01,412 --> 00:20:04,514
and a line we don't cross.

439
00:20:08,385 --> 00:20:09,251
Right.

440
00:20:10,221 --> 00:20:12,688
So I'm trying
to be a little more careful with you.

441
00:20:14,159 --> 00:20:15,758
You're trying to be careful with me?

442
00:20:16,322 --> 00:20:18,828
- I'm just being more cautious.
- You're being cautious.

443
00:20:19,331 --> 00:20:22,232
I'm not as comfortable with you
as I am with Ji Hye.

444
00:20:23,801 --> 00:20:25,234
Hearing Jung Won say things like that,

445
00:20:25,235 --> 00:20:28,204
it really does seem like...

446
00:20:28,205 --> 00:20:29,906
he's torn between the two women.

447
00:20:30,107 --> 00:20:33,042
From what he said, it seems like...

448
00:20:33,043 --> 00:20:34,410
he's interested in Jin Young.

449
00:20:34,411 --> 00:20:36,112
(Who is Jung Won's heart leaning toward?)

450
00:20:37,048 --> 00:20:39,649
Well, actually, you're probably the one...

451
00:20:39,817 --> 00:20:41,185
I'm most uncomfortable around.

452
00:20:42,152 --> 00:20:43,619
Well, not exactly comfortable.

453
00:20:44,021 --> 00:20:45,855
Just not at ease when we're talking.

454
00:20:45,923 --> 00:20:49,059
I knew you'd be coming today...

455
00:20:49,060 --> 00:20:51,394
because I picked you.

456
00:20:51,829 --> 00:20:52,796
While I was waiting for you,

457
00:20:52,797 --> 00:20:56,733
I kept wondering
what I should even talk to you about.

458
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,000
- You did?
- Yes.

459
00:20:58,705 --> 00:21:00,778
There's no need to come up
with conversation topics.

460
00:21:00,779 --> 00:21:02,646
Just go
wherever the conversation takes you.

461
00:21:03,014 --> 00:21:03,847
You're right.

462
00:21:09,854 --> 00:21:11,988
But I think...

463
00:21:12,091 --> 00:21:15,459
it's really cute
when you get that nervous.

464
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,360
It's funny too.

465
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,467
Did you bring that book with you?

466
00:21:24,602 --> 00:21:25,402
Well,

467
00:21:27,239 --> 00:21:30,173
Bye. I guess it's time for you to go.

468
00:21:30,575 --> 00:21:31,608
I've got to go now.

469
00:21:33,211 --> 00:21:34,077
Bye.

470
00:21:34,299 --> 00:21:35,600
(Cool words, but a not-so-cool expression)

471
00:21:35,601 --> 00:21:36,513
Have fun.

472
00:21:37,248 --> 00:21:39,015
You don't even know what I'm going to do.

473
00:21:39,350 --> 00:21:41,584
- You don't know what I'll do.
- I'm just saying.

474
00:21:42,787 --> 00:21:44,187
Then, I'll see you back at the house.

475
00:21:47,826 --> 00:21:50,027
Okay. I'll just be resting there.

476
00:21:50,028 --> 00:21:52,363
(Jin Young and Jung Won's
day-drinking date comes to an end.)

477
00:21:52,364 --> 00:21:53,164
See you later.

478
00:21:56,701 --> 00:21:58,502
It brings back old memories.

479
00:22:00,705 --> 00:22:01,739
(The second day-drinking date)

480
00:22:01,740 --> 00:22:02,606
I wonder who it'll be.

481
00:22:04,876 --> 00:22:09,746
(An older woman waits
while touching up her makeup.)

482
00:22:09,747 --> 00:22:10,714
It's Ji Hye.

483
00:22:10,715 --> 00:22:12,616
(Ji Hye)

484
00:22:13,418 --> 00:22:17,388
(The younger guy Ji Hye wants
to have a day drink with is...)

485
00:22:18,857 --> 00:22:22,860
(Ji Hye can't stop smiling
as soon as she sees her date.)

486
00:22:23,094 --> 00:22:25,295
I can't help smiling
whenever I see your face.

487
00:22:25,296 --> 00:22:26,730
I crack up whenever I look into your eyes.

488
00:22:26,831 --> 00:22:28,366
They're really showing
these two dates back-to-back?

489
00:22:29,234 --> 00:22:31,135
Wow, this place has
such a great atmosphere.

490
00:22:31,136 --> 00:22:32,369
This is the best way to compare them.

491
00:22:32,370 --> 00:22:33,737
Where did you go before this date?

492
00:22:34,072 --> 00:22:36,407
- Somewhere nice?
- Yes, somewhere nice.

493
00:22:36,408 --> 00:22:38,276
And I picked a place like this?

494
00:22:38,810 --> 00:22:39,811
This place is nice too.

495
00:22:41,312 --> 00:22:42,946
- Was this the right choice?
- Sure.

496
00:22:42,981 --> 00:22:44,448
- Have you eaten?
- What?

497
00:22:44,449 --> 00:22:45,849
- Have you eaten?
- Yes, I had a little.

498
00:22:46,084 --> 00:22:47,918
So what are we drinking today?

499
00:22:48,887 --> 00:22:49,820
Beer.

500
00:22:51,122 --> 00:22:51,823
Beer?

501
00:22:51,824 --> 00:22:55,258
I want either dried pollock and egg soup
or spicy silkworm pupa stew.

502
00:22:56,861 --> 00:22:58,495
- Well...
- One of those.

503
00:22:58,496 --> 00:23:00,530
Then let's just have dried pollock
and egg soup with soju.

504
00:23:01,332 --> 00:23:02,632
Beer doesn't match well with that.

505
00:23:04,269 --> 00:23:05,737
They laugh the moment
either of them speaks.

506
00:23:05,738 --> 00:23:06,604
What are they laughing about?

507
00:23:06,605 --> 00:23:08,939
What's so funny
about the menu she mentioned?

508
00:23:09,841 --> 00:23:11,842
- Did you have fun on your date?
- What?

509
00:23:12,244 --> 00:23:13,543
Yes, it was alright.

510
00:23:15,046 --> 00:23:16,013
You should've said you didn't.

511
00:23:17,315 --> 00:23:18,282
Why are you being so honest?

512
00:23:18,283 --> 00:23:19,616
Honesty is always good.

513
00:23:20,084 --> 00:23:22,185
- You're right. It is.
- I'm sure you'll make this more fun.

514
00:23:24,823 --> 00:23:25,856
You can do it, Ji Hye.

515
00:23:26,825 --> 00:23:28,325
It'll be all right.

516
00:23:28,326 --> 00:23:29,660
- Good?
- What is?

517
00:23:29,661 --> 00:23:32,229
- Are you okay drinking without any food?
- I don't mind.

518
00:23:33,364 --> 00:23:34,399
Those two look great together.

519
00:23:34,899 --> 00:23:35,966
They really do.

520
00:23:36,868 --> 00:23:38,335
This soju tastes good.

521
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:40,392
You can really hold your liquor well.

522
00:23:41,072 --> 00:23:41,937
Not really.

523
00:23:43,007 --> 00:23:47,043
This is what I feel.

524
00:23:47,912 --> 00:23:51,081
We said we'd spend some time
getting to know everyone first, right?

525
00:23:51,366 --> 00:23:53,100
And that ended up lasting longer
than we expected.

526
00:23:53,318 --> 00:23:54,184
True.

527
00:23:55,653 --> 00:23:57,921
I said I wanted to take the time
to get to know everyone first.

528
00:23:57,922 --> 00:23:59,190
I said that I'd express my feelings...

529
00:23:59,191 --> 00:24:02,059
once I'd made up my mind,
and that was yesterday.

530
00:24:03,027 --> 00:24:05,429
But I've never lied to you.

531
00:24:05,530 --> 00:24:08,699
But what if my feelings changed
during that time?

532
00:24:09,434 --> 00:24:10,332
Then I'd be sad.

533
00:24:11,402 --> 00:24:12,503
I'd be sad and regret it.

534
00:24:12,504 --> 00:24:14,105
I'd think I should've shown you
how I felt sooner.

535
00:24:14,639 --> 00:24:15,772
So, you think your feelings have changed?

536
00:24:15,773 --> 00:24:16,473
Being sad?

537
00:24:16,908 --> 00:24:17,708
Have you changed your mind?

538
00:24:18,477 --> 00:24:19,776
I don't know.

539
00:24:19,878 --> 00:24:23,280
But if I have, do you think
you could win me back?

540
00:24:24,349 --> 00:24:26,417
- Yes.
- You answered without even thinking?

541
00:24:26,418 --> 00:24:27,551
I think I could.

542
00:24:31,823 --> 00:24:33,857
I don't know how it'll all turn out,

543
00:24:33,858 --> 00:24:35,926
but I'm not that worried.

544
00:24:40,031 --> 00:24:43,433
So your feelings have never changed?

545
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:47,638
Well, you've always been my first choice.

546
00:24:47,639 --> 00:24:49,506
You're the one I click with the most.

547
00:24:49,507 --> 00:24:51,041
And I have the most fun when I'm with you.

548
00:24:51,642 --> 00:24:53,777
One thing I liked was...

549
00:24:54,646 --> 00:24:56,814
that whenever I was with the other guys,

550
00:24:58,082 --> 00:25:00,216
I really felt the age gap.

551
00:25:00,952 --> 00:25:03,253
They all felt noticeably younger.

552
00:25:04,355 --> 00:25:05,955
But I don't feel that way with you.

553
00:25:06,658 --> 00:25:10,027
You never come across as immature.

554
00:25:12,296 --> 00:25:14,164
And I saw it too.

555
00:25:14,165 --> 00:25:16,666
I saw you talking with Jin Young.

556
00:25:17,168 --> 00:25:19,302
She definitely made her feelings
for you pretty clear.

557
00:25:19,570 --> 00:25:21,004
She did? I do like when someone...

558
00:25:22,107 --> 00:25:23,306
is open about how they feel.

559
00:25:24,075 --> 00:25:24,875
I will be.

560
00:25:27,111 --> 00:25:28,579
Now you've left me with nothing to say.

561
00:25:29,614 --> 00:25:32,182
- You've left me with nothing to say.
- I'll express myself openly.

562
00:25:33,451 --> 00:25:34,651
I really appreciated what you did.

563
00:25:35,053 --> 00:25:35,953
I'd told you that I hadn't felt...

564
00:25:35,954 --> 00:25:38,455
that you were interested in me
and that I wanted you...

565
00:25:38,456 --> 00:25:39,823
to be a little more forward.

566
00:25:40,124 --> 00:25:42,659
That was when I saw the side of you...

567
00:25:42,660 --> 00:25:43,793
that I'd been hoping to see.

568
00:25:44,729 --> 00:25:45,696
- You mean yesterday?
- Most women...

569
00:25:45,697 --> 00:25:50,301
Yes. Most people would've
just brushed it off,

570
00:25:50,302 --> 00:25:53,303
but you were like,
"Okay, then I'll be more forward."

571
00:25:55,006 --> 00:25:56,340
I think that's exactly...

572
00:25:57,342 --> 00:25:59,276
the kind of easygoing nature
I'm attracted to.

573
00:25:59,277 --> 00:26:04,648
I like a woman
who's able to take the lead with me.

574
00:26:05,116 --> 00:26:06,116
I'm exactly the same.

575
00:26:06,517 --> 00:26:07,350
Because...

576
00:26:07,752 --> 00:26:10,620
I'm attracted to a woman
who takes the lead in the relationship.

577
00:26:10,621 --> 00:26:11,454
Me too.

578
00:26:11,889 --> 00:26:13,022
They both need someone more assertive.

579
00:26:14,525 --> 00:26:16,092
What did you talk about with Jin Young?

580
00:26:16,494 --> 00:26:17,727
- Is it okay to ask?
- Sure.

581
00:26:17,829 --> 00:26:18,895
So she's completely sure?

582
00:26:19,330 --> 00:26:20,263
She is.

583
00:26:21,866 --> 00:26:22,766
Very impressive.

584
00:26:23,568 --> 00:26:25,235
Does that mean
we're basically headed for a 2-on-1 date?

585
00:26:28,139 --> 00:26:32,576
When I talked to Jin Young today,

586
00:26:32,710 --> 00:26:35,879
it felt like we were on a blind date.

587
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:38,782
That was the kind of atmosphere.

588
00:26:39,550 --> 00:26:41,017
It's not like I dislike that kind of vibe,

589
00:26:41,018 --> 00:26:42,385
but it was like a serious blind date.

590
00:26:43,254 --> 00:26:44,187
However, when I'm with you,

591
00:26:44,622 --> 00:26:46,723
everything just feels
so much more casual and natural.

592
00:26:47,525 --> 00:26:48,792
That's a compliment, right?

593
00:26:48,793 --> 00:26:50,760
It is. I mean I feel comfortable with you.

594
00:26:50,761 --> 00:26:51,628
Right. Exactly.

595
00:26:51,629 --> 00:26:54,431
It feels like we just met up
without making any plans.

596
00:26:54,966 --> 00:26:55,766
Exactly.

597
00:26:58,302 --> 00:26:59,535
One thing I'm sure about is...

598
00:27:00,338 --> 00:27:03,206
that things are going
to get pretty awkward...

599
00:27:03,641 --> 00:27:04,607
back at the house.

600
00:27:04,608 --> 00:27:06,376
Why? I think everything's already decided.

601
00:27:06,377 --> 00:27:07,143
You do?

602
00:27:07,144 --> 00:27:09,112
Isn't it?

603
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,280
Have you made up your mind?

604
00:27:12,050 --> 00:27:13,117
I'm still figuring that out.

605
00:27:18,589 --> 00:27:21,459
He has both older women wrapped
around his finger emotionally.

606
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:23,893
You have to reassure me.

607
00:27:25,763 --> 00:27:26,696
I know.

608
00:27:28,566 --> 00:27:29,332
And I will.

609
00:27:30,835 --> 00:27:31,635
I will.

610
00:27:35,139 --> 00:27:37,040
I didn't know something
like this could happen.

611
00:27:37,575 --> 00:27:38,408
What?

612
00:27:39,710 --> 00:27:41,310
This is the first time
this has ever happened to me.

613
00:27:41,311 --> 00:27:42,645
(Laughing)

614
00:27:42,646 --> 00:27:43,346
I'm serious.

615
00:27:43,482 --> 00:27:46,684
I've never had to compete
with another woman...

616
00:27:46,685 --> 00:27:49,620
over a man before.

617
00:27:49,621 --> 00:27:50,420
Neither have I.

618
00:27:50,789 --> 00:27:54,258
I figured you hadn't. I used to think
I could win any guy over.

619
00:27:54,259 --> 00:27:55,159
Sure.

620
00:27:55,593 --> 00:27:56,426
I'd think,

621
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:57,727
You could win him over?

622
00:27:57,728 --> 00:27:59,462
"What's the problem?
I'll just win him over."

623
00:27:59,463 --> 00:28:00,930
That's how I used to think.

624
00:28:00,931 --> 00:28:03,333
But now that I'm actually
in this situation,

625
00:28:03,534 --> 00:28:06,603
part of me wonders if I should step aside.

626
00:28:07,773 --> 00:28:09,506
Then I stop myself and think, "No."

627
00:28:10,541 --> 00:28:11,574
That's right. No.

628
00:28:12,443 --> 00:28:14,477
No. I have to give it a shot
at least once.

629
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:18,248
If it still doesn't work out after that,
then I think I'll back off.

630
00:28:19,317 --> 00:28:20,331
So you won't back off right now?

631
00:28:20,551 --> 00:28:21,317
Of course not.

632
00:28:22,653 --> 00:28:23,519
Absolutely not.

633
00:28:24,922 --> 00:28:27,891
I've never expressed my feelings
to a man like this before in my life.

634
00:28:28,393 --> 00:28:29,393
I mean it.

635
00:28:29,727 --> 00:28:31,228
You're really putting yourself out there.

636
00:28:31,229 --> 00:28:33,096
- I really am.
- You are. You're really making an effort.

637
00:28:33,798 --> 00:28:36,166
Here I am, at this age,

638
00:28:36,268 --> 00:28:38,334
trying to win a guy over.

639
00:28:38,604 --> 00:28:42,539
Trying to win over a 29-year-old man.

640
00:28:45,577 --> 00:28:46,476
It's ridiculous.

641
00:28:47,712 --> 00:28:48,678
You really want to win me over?

642
00:28:49,413 --> 00:28:51,081
I thought I already had.

643
00:28:51,082 --> 00:28:52,615
Goodness.

644
00:28:53,417 --> 00:28:55,385
Actually, never mind. Let's stop there.

645
00:28:55,386 --> 00:28:55,907
Sure.

646
00:28:55,908 --> 00:28:57,253
(Which older woman
will he choose in the end?)

647
00:28:57,622 --> 00:28:59,590
What is it about Jung Won
that's so attractive?

648
00:28:59,591 --> 00:29:01,858
Why are the older women so drawn to him?

649
00:29:01,859 --> 00:29:06,463
I think it's probably how relaxed
he seems.

650
00:29:06,931 --> 00:29:09,867
The other younger guys seem...

651
00:29:09,868 --> 00:29:13,403
completely consumed
by the women they're interested in,

652
00:29:13,404 --> 00:29:16,773
but Jung Won gives off the feeling
that he'll be fine either way.

653
00:29:16,774 --> 00:29:19,410
I guess it's important
to carry yourself...

654
00:29:19,411 --> 00:29:22,823
with that kind of ease,
even if you don't have much.

655
00:29:22,847 --> 00:29:24,715
(Totally.)

656
00:29:26,017 --> 00:29:29,453
(A private glamping spot
just for the two of them...)

657
00:29:29,454 --> 00:29:33,190
(by the riverside)

658
00:29:33,824 --> 00:29:38,961
(Who did Yu Jin choose
for the day-drinking date?)

659
00:29:41,465 --> 00:29:43,266
(Grinning)

660
00:29:43,668 --> 00:29:46,503
(Yu Jin's day-drinking date)

661
00:29:46,504 --> 00:29:47,505
(Si Won)

662
00:29:47,506 --> 00:29:49,239
- It's so different.
- He's smiling from ear to ear.

663
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:51,174
(So nice to see you!)

664
00:29:51,375 --> 00:29:52,775
Where were you before coming here?

665
00:29:54,846 --> 00:29:58,815
I was hoping Yu Jin would ask me
out on a date.

666
00:30:00,166 --> 00:30:03,099
The date with her yesterday was amazing.

667
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:04,200
He said it was amazing.

668
00:30:04,566 --> 00:30:07,839
So I wanted to go on a date
with her again.

669
00:30:09,300 --> 00:30:11,443
I just want to have fun with her.

670
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,399
Look at this.

671
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,899
We're glamping today.

672
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:15,733
What's all this?

673
00:30:17,100 --> 00:30:19,299
I guess you've already had a few drinks.

674
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:20,466
Your face is red.

675
00:30:20,900 --> 00:30:21,665
- Really?
- Yes.

676
00:30:21,666 --> 00:30:22,954
You're blushing.

677
00:30:23,366 --> 00:30:25,099
- Right here and here.
- Is that so?

678
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:26,932
- Did you talk to her?
- Yes.

679
00:30:26,933 --> 00:30:28,065
Guess who.

680
00:30:28,066 --> 00:30:29,461
Didn't you talk to Ji Seung?

681
00:30:29,566 --> 00:30:31,400
- You're right.
- Come on.

682
00:30:32,133 --> 00:30:34,332
- The way he talks is so different.
- Did the talk go well?

683
00:30:34,333 --> 00:30:35,133
Yes.

684
00:30:36,008 --> 00:30:37,475
I'll tell you what we talked about later.

685
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:38,800
Really?

686
00:30:41,366 --> 00:30:46,366
(Si Won went on a date
with Ji Seung first.)

687
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:49,366
So there's no one else
you want to get to know anymore?

688
00:30:49,733 --> 00:30:51,100
- Yes.
- Is that so?

689
00:30:51,433 --> 00:30:52,384
You won't regret it?

690
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,486
I don't think I will.

691
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:58,490
What about you?
What are you going to do now?

692
00:30:58,866 --> 00:30:59,900
- From now on?
- Yes.

693
00:31:02,266 --> 00:31:05,499
From now on, I think I'm going to focus
on the one person I'm interested in.

694
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:06,333
Really?

695
00:31:14,033 --> 00:31:15,165
What's your plan?

696
00:31:15,166 --> 00:31:16,508
Do you have something in mind?

697
00:31:17,300 --> 00:31:20,412
I'm not sure. What can I do
when we only have two days left?

698
00:31:21,266 --> 00:31:23,315
Well, you should express your feelings
as much as you can.

699
00:31:24,366 --> 00:31:26,500
Can you actually do that?

700
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:29,500
Even if it feels tough,
you should give it a shot.

701
00:31:32,733 --> 00:31:37,933
(Si Won honestly tells Ji Seung
how he feels.)

702
00:31:38,733 --> 00:31:39,633
Did you?

703
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,165
I think I'm going to stay
with Ju Hee tonight.

704
00:31:43,166 --> 00:31:45,537
I know. It might be awkward for you.

705
00:31:46,433 --> 00:31:47,665
Would it?

706
00:31:47,666 --> 00:31:49,765
- Maybe I should just crash here.
- I know.

707
00:31:49,766 --> 00:31:51,510
- Let's crash here together.
- We should.

708
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:53,865
"Let's crash here together?"

709
00:31:53,866 --> 00:31:55,000
What?

710
00:31:56,566 --> 00:31:58,266
I didn't know you were such a player!

711
00:31:58,633 --> 00:31:59,466
For real?

712
00:31:59,766 --> 00:32:01,799
- My goodness.
- That's huge.

713
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:02,866
Well said.

714
00:32:03,133 --> 00:32:04,599
Let's crash here together.

715
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:06,099
- We have a bed here.
- I know.

716
00:32:06,100 --> 00:32:07,165
It's nice here.

717
00:32:07,166 --> 00:32:08,599
We have a bathroom too.

718
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:09,965
- That's a bathroom.
- Really?

719
00:32:09,966 --> 00:32:10,733
Yes.

720
00:32:11,366 --> 00:32:12,800
That's amazing.

721
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:14,766
Can you build a fire?

722
00:32:15,033 --> 00:32:16,900
I won't know unless I try.

723
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:20,265
I kind of wanted to try it.

724
00:32:20,266 --> 00:32:22,207
- Shall we build a fire then?
- Let's try it together.

725
00:32:22,900 --> 00:32:24,765
- You're hungry, right?
- Yes.

726
00:32:24,766 --> 00:32:26,366
- Right?
- I'm a little hungry today.

727
00:32:26,700 --> 00:32:29,266
(Si Won builds a fire with ease.)

728
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,465
- Should we put it on the fire now?
- Yes.

729
00:32:31,466 --> 00:32:32,851
Do you think you can handle it?

730
00:32:33,366 --> 00:32:34,966
I'll do my best.

731
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,424
It looks so good.

732
00:32:40,833 --> 00:32:42,365
- We have two days left.
- Yes.

733
00:32:42,366 --> 00:32:44,308
Who will you go on a date with tomorrow
if we get the chance?

734
00:32:44,333 --> 00:32:45,399
Who else?

735
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,665
Who are you going to choose?

736
00:32:47,866 --> 00:32:48,755
Well, I will...

737
00:32:48,779 --> 00:32:50,366
Do you know Choi Yu Jin?

738
00:32:51,100 --> 00:32:52,632
Hey!

739
00:32:52,633 --> 00:32:54,033
(What was that?)

740
00:32:54,233 --> 00:32:55,200
It's over.

741
00:32:56,133 --> 00:32:57,965
- You're making this hard for us.
- It's over for them.

742
00:32:57,966 --> 00:32:59,632
We're human too!

743
00:32:59,633 --> 00:33:02,000
Imagine how wonderful that would be.

744
00:33:02,366 --> 00:33:06,266
She was so worried
because of their 12-year age gap.

745
00:33:06,566 --> 00:33:08,653
Now that he keeps telling her,
"You're the one,"

746
00:33:09,233 --> 00:33:10,455
I'd definitely go for him.

747
00:33:10,632 --> 00:33:11,743
Well, I will...

748
00:33:11,768 --> 00:33:15,226
Do you know Choi Yu Jin?

749
00:33:15,251 --> 00:33:16,941
(Feeling shy)

750
00:33:16,966 --> 00:33:19,432
I have someone too.

751
00:33:19,433 --> 00:33:21,465
She's so happy making somaek.

752
00:33:21,466 --> 00:33:22,832
- It's a secret.
- Is it a secret?

753
00:33:22,833 --> 00:33:23,935
Yes, it's a secret.

754
00:33:24,233 --> 00:33:26,366
- Someone who looks like Ok Taec Yeon.
- Ok Taec Yeon?

755
00:33:26,833 --> 00:33:28,866
He really does look like him.

756
00:33:30,166 --> 00:33:33,100
(The meat is cooked to perfection.)

757
00:33:33,666 --> 00:33:34,766
Try it first.

758
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:40,666
(He hands over the first piece
to hungry Yu Jin.)

759
00:33:41,166 --> 00:33:42,133
Tell me if you like it.

760
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:46,791
Why? Is it too hot?

761
00:33:47,066 --> 00:33:48,432
It's different. It's so good.

762
00:33:48,433 --> 00:33:49,466
- Really?
- Yes.

763
00:33:51,033 --> 00:33:53,633
It's totally different
from pan-cooked barbecue.

764
00:33:54,166 --> 00:33:56,165
You should try it now. It's really good.

765
00:33:56,166 --> 00:33:57,400
- Is it all cooked?
- Yes!

766
00:33:58,866 --> 00:34:01,033
(Si Won takes a bite as well.)

767
00:34:01,766 --> 00:34:03,542
- You're right. It's really good.
- Right?

768
00:34:04,766 --> 00:34:06,032
You're a great cook.

769
00:34:06,033 --> 00:34:06,933
- Really?
- Yes.

770
00:34:07,466 --> 00:34:09,265
I love how expressive you are.

771
00:34:09,266 --> 00:34:10,266
- Really?
- Yes.

772
00:34:10,566 --> 00:34:12,532
I guess you could say that.

773
00:34:12,533 --> 00:34:13,600
That's a compliment.

774
00:34:14,033 --> 00:34:15,732
You said even your type has changed.

775
00:34:15,733 --> 00:34:17,632
Yes, my type...

776
00:34:17,633 --> 00:34:19,065
You said it hasn't completely changed,

777
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:20,521
but the balance
between how much you value...

778
00:34:20,545 --> 00:34:22,484
Yes, personality versus appearance.

779
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:27,165
Thinking back, the people I've dated...

780
00:34:27,166 --> 00:34:28,932
had personalities similar to yours.

781
00:34:28,933 --> 00:34:30,733
They were calm and steady.

782
00:34:31,166 --> 00:34:33,665
They were all stable.

783
00:34:33,666 --> 00:34:35,899
But they were all older
or the same age as you, right?

784
00:34:35,900 --> 00:34:36,965
- Yes.
- Right?

785
00:34:36,966 --> 00:34:39,099
- They were mostly around my age.
- You mostly date people your age.

786
00:34:39,100 --> 00:34:41,699
I want my relationship
to feel like a friendship.

787
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:42,500
So...

788
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:45,233
But based on yesterday,
we seem compatible.

789
00:34:46,866 --> 00:34:48,733
- You felt that on the date?
- Yes.

790
00:34:49,900 --> 00:34:52,033
I felt like I was dating an older guy.

791
00:34:52,466 --> 00:34:53,700
My goodness.

792
00:34:54,733 --> 00:34:56,399
Should I add about 13 years or something?

793
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,399
I can't really feel the age gap
between them either.

794
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,599
- That's true.
- Right.

795
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:01,899
I think I'm kind of used to it now.

796
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:03,432
But it's almost over.

797
00:35:03,433 --> 00:35:04,466
(Their time in Yeon House
is drawing to a close.)

798
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,500
- It felt short, right?
- Yes.

799
00:35:08,500 --> 00:35:11,233
Now that we all have
to go back to reality,

800
00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:12,833
I'm worried.

801
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:16,766
- After filming this?
- Yes.

802
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:22,400
I'm worried if I can just slip back
into my old ways.

803
00:35:23,133 --> 00:35:24,432
Am I in a dream?

804
00:35:24,433 --> 00:35:27,265
It'll feel like a dream
once we go back, right?

805
00:35:27,266 --> 00:35:28,300
I know.

806
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:33,500
- They can stay in that dream.
- Exactly.

807
00:35:34,233 --> 00:35:37,133
(Yu Jin and Si Won are on their way back.)

808
00:35:39,866 --> 00:35:41,406
What do you think about a 12-year age gap?

809
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:44,366
(Bursting into laughter)

810
00:35:45,500 --> 00:35:46,332
He's tipsy.

811
00:35:46,333 --> 00:35:48,332
Now he's going to say
what he really thinks.

812
00:35:48,333 --> 00:35:50,800
(Can't wait.)

813
00:35:51,300 --> 00:35:52,917
What do you think about a 12-year age gap?

814
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:55,899
(Bursting into laughter)

815
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:57,633
I wanted to ask you this directly
at least once.

816
00:35:58,666 --> 00:36:01,099
About that, I mean...

817
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:03,595
Everyone asked me why I was so shocked.

818
00:36:04,333 --> 00:36:05,966
- After the age reveal?
- Yes.

819
00:36:06,733 --> 00:36:11,133
They said, "Didn't you expect
there to be an age difference?"

820
00:36:11,666 --> 00:36:12,932
- Here's what I said.
- Yes, the age.

821
00:36:12,933 --> 00:36:15,040
"I knew there'd be one,
but I didn't think it'd happen to me."

822
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:19,700
It was something I had never imagined.

823
00:36:20,133 --> 00:36:23,766
But when I'm talking to you,
I don't think about that at all.

824
00:36:25,233 --> 00:36:28,099
- As long as we don't bring it up?
- Yes, as long as we don't.

825
00:36:28,100 --> 00:36:29,272
But from time to time,

826
00:36:29,296 --> 00:36:31,565
when you talk about your military service,
or about...

827
00:36:31,566 --> 00:36:33,865
- how your friends used to fool around.
- Or about college.

828
00:36:33,866 --> 00:36:35,865
Yes, or about college.

829
00:36:35,866 --> 00:36:37,562
That reminds me
that you're 12 years younger.

830
00:36:38,166 --> 00:36:40,300
That we share
the same Chinese zodiac sign.

831
00:36:44,466 --> 00:36:48,733
But I don't feel the difference
when it's just the two of us like this.

832
00:36:49,700 --> 00:36:53,165
Still, when I focus solely
on the 12-year age gap,

833
00:36:53,166 --> 00:36:55,865
it's not easy.

834
00:36:55,866 --> 00:36:57,100
No, it's not.

835
00:36:57,900 --> 00:36:58,933
What do you think?

836
00:36:59,166 --> 00:37:00,266
- Me?
- Yes.

837
00:37:01,733 --> 00:37:04,332
I've never dated
someone 12 years older than me.

838
00:37:04,333 --> 00:37:05,133
Right.

839
00:37:06,666 --> 00:37:09,432
But if I can forget about that on a date,

840
00:37:09,433 --> 00:37:12,333
I think it could work.
That's what I think.

841
00:37:12,666 --> 00:37:15,800
So I'd like to go on a date
in the real world.

842
00:37:17,300 --> 00:37:19,199
- When we're done with this?
- Yes.

843
00:37:19,200 --> 00:37:21,566
- In our actual daily lives.
- In reality.

844
00:37:24,533 --> 00:37:26,132
I can't wait to go on a date with you.

845
00:37:26,133 --> 00:37:27,833
- We should get hagfish.
- We really should.

846
00:37:29,300 --> 00:37:32,399
Hagfish... Wait, that's expensive.

847
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,332
Really?

848
00:37:33,333 --> 00:37:34,433
(The two promise to go on a date
in the real world.)

849
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:38,441
They're going to become a real couple.

850
00:37:38,466 --> 00:37:39,932
That's a full confession.

851
00:37:39,933 --> 00:37:42,065
Watching this makes me realize...

852
00:37:42,066 --> 00:37:45,165
that even though they're
in different chapters of their lives,

853
00:37:45,166 --> 00:37:47,932
with him in his 20s
and her in her mid-30s,

854
00:37:47,933 --> 00:37:52,299
and if you tear out those pages
and put them together,

855
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:55,232
they can fall in love with each other.

856
00:37:55,233 --> 00:37:56,499
- That's a nice way to put it.
- Age...

857
00:37:56,500 --> 00:37:57,765
Age doesn't matter at all.

858
00:37:57,766 --> 00:37:59,611
They just never had the chance
to cross paths.

859
00:37:59,866 --> 00:38:02,800
They couldn't love each other
because they were in different chapters.

860
00:38:03,333 --> 00:38:08,032
- Once we created that chance for them,
- In Yeon House.

861
00:38:08,033 --> 00:38:09,999
it just clicked.

862
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,689
What a sweet way to put it.

863
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:17,500
(The older women's choice:
the fifth day-drinking date)

864
00:38:18,533 --> 00:38:21,265
(Who is waiting for her date to arrive?)

865
00:38:21,266 --> 00:38:22,865
(Ju Hee)

866
00:38:22,866 --> 00:38:23,868
Yun So and Ju Hee!

867
00:38:26,466 --> 00:38:30,166
(Is Ju Hee's final date Yun So?)

868
00:38:34,033 --> 00:38:36,132
(Who is Ju Hee's day-drinking date?)

869
00:38:36,133 --> 00:38:38,366
(It's Yun So.)

870
00:38:39,133 --> 00:38:40,800
(Grinning)

871
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,520
Have you been waiting long?

872
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:44,332
- A little.
- Really?

873
00:38:44,333 --> 00:38:45,100
How long?

874
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:47,659
How long have I been waiting?

875
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,295
- A little.
- A little!

876
00:38:51,566 --> 00:38:53,900
Why does Yun So look so cool now?

877
00:38:55,353 --> 00:38:56,965
- Because he's confident.
- He's different from the start.

878
00:38:56,966 --> 00:38:58,536
Confidence is everything.

879
00:39:00,500 --> 00:39:02,907
I hoped it would be you. I'm glad.

880
00:39:05,700 --> 00:39:07,099
- Here's your food.
- Thank you.

881
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:08,399
I ordered for us.

882
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,566
- You took care of everything, didn't you?
- I did.

883
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,132
- Guess we're on our own for service.
- Looks like it.

884
00:39:14,133 --> 00:39:15,486
I thought he'd pour it for us.

885
00:39:16,233 --> 00:39:17,300
He's using both hands.

886
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:18,957
How should I do this?

887
00:39:19,833 --> 00:39:20,999
How should I? Just like this?

888
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:22,065
You can use one hand.

889
00:39:22,066 --> 00:39:22,833
With one hand?

890
00:39:23,633 --> 00:39:24,832
You pour wine with one hand.

891
00:39:24,833 --> 00:39:26,966
I've never had wine before.

892
00:39:27,433 --> 00:39:30,165
That's total younger-boyfriend vibes.

893
00:39:30,166 --> 00:39:31,032
He's cute.

894
00:39:31,033 --> 00:39:32,165
(Yun So pours the first glass of wine
for Ju Hee.)

895
00:39:32,166 --> 00:39:33,066
Now it's your turn.

896
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,165
What was this?

897
00:39:36,166 --> 00:39:38,499
I've never had wine before.

898
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:40,933
(Now Ju Hee fills Yun So's glass.)

899
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:42,033
I see.

900
00:39:43,433 --> 00:39:45,733
Should we swirl and smell it
before drinking?

901
00:39:46,166 --> 00:39:47,552
Have you really never had it?

902
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:50,132
I never had the chance.

903
00:39:50,133 --> 00:39:51,232
- For real?
- Yes.

904
00:39:51,233 --> 00:39:53,332
- Guys usually don't get the chance.
- Yes.

905
00:39:53,333 --> 00:39:56,432
I think guys start drinking wine
later than women.

906
00:39:56,433 --> 00:39:59,832
I didn't drink wine when I was 24.

907
00:39:59,864 --> 00:40:01,264
When you were 24,

908
00:40:01,265 --> 00:40:03,266
wine wasn't so popular in Korea.

909
00:40:03,284 --> 00:40:04,377
(Glaring)

910
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:05,203
I'm sorry.

911
00:40:05,737 --> 00:40:06,570
You're right, though.

912
00:40:14,379 --> 00:40:15,546
(Savoring)

913
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:21,118
- How is it?
- It's good.

914
00:40:25,824 --> 00:40:26,891
So what do you think?

915
00:40:27,325 --> 00:40:28,625
What? Being with you?

916
00:40:29,427 --> 00:40:30,193
Yes.

917
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:32,796
I love it. What about you?

918
00:40:33,064 --> 00:40:36,032
Ju Hee really likes Yun So now.

919
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:37,835
Did you have any questions?

920
00:40:39,537 --> 00:40:40,570
- For you?
- Yes.

921
00:40:42,206 --> 00:40:44,007
(Thinking)

922
00:40:47,011 --> 00:40:48,244
Our age gap...

923
00:40:49,647 --> 00:40:51,181
- is 11 years.
- Yes.

924
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:53,483
Can you really date me?

925
00:40:55,186 --> 00:40:56,119
That caught her off guard.

926
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,855
(Ju Hee hesitates to answer.)

927
00:40:58,856 --> 00:41:00,824
You said you'd be fine...

928
00:41:02,493 --> 00:41:03,660
if the gap was 5 or 6 years,

929
00:41:03,661 --> 00:41:07,130
but it'd be hard if it was bigger.

930
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:11,201
Can you really date someone...

931
00:41:11,903 --> 00:41:12,937
who's 11 years younger?

932
00:41:12,938 --> 00:41:15,138
If you really like that person.

933
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:16,306
(Yun So wants to hear her true feelings.)

934
00:41:16,441 --> 00:41:18,976
If I thought I couldn't,

935
00:41:19,811 --> 00:41:21,078
I wouldn't be here.

936
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:22,545
Also,

937
00:41:23,514 --> 00:41:24,481
I'm...

938
00:41:24,883 --> 00:41:27,351
just seeing you for who you are.

939
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,121
When I heard your age,

940
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:36,226
I wished I was older.

941
00:41:36,893 --> 00:41:38,062
I've never felt that way before.

942
00:41:38,763 --> 00:41:41,998
I wanted to be much older
for the first time in my life.

943
00:41:42,734 --> 00:41:44,768
That doesn't sound so great.

944
00:41:44,769 --> 00:41:46,537
"Much older."

945
00:41:46,538 --> 00:41:49,073
He's not just saying
he wishes he was older.

946
00:41:49,074 --> 00:41:50,208
"Much older."

947
00:41:50,775 --> 00:41:52,518
It hurt her feelings a bit.

948
00:41:52,543 --> 00:41:54,110
It's not that. He went too far.

949
00:41:54,712 --> 00:41:56,646
He shouldn't have put it that way.

950
00:41:56,647 --> 00:41:58,249
Ju Hee was having a good time,

951
00:41:58,483 --> 00:41:59,617
but that made her pause.

952
00:42:00,919 --> 00:42:04,287
I wanted to be much older
for the first time in my life.

953
00:42:05,156 --> 00:42:06,691
What kind of confession is that?

954
00:42:06,891 --> 00:42:09,059
Let's say...

955
00:42:09,961 --> 00:42:11,895
love is at 100 percent.

956
00:42:12,531 --> 00:42:15,098
Some people start there,
and some start from zero...

957
00:42:15,099 --> 00:42:16,766
- Yes.
- and build up.

958
00:42:17,435 --> 00:42:20,938
I'm someone who starts at zero
and builds up.

959
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:24,308
Ever since I first saw you,

960
00:42:25,043 --> 00:42:28,412
my feelings have only grown.

961
00:42:29,013 --> 00:42:30,681
Your first impression was so strong.

962
00:42:31,049 --> 00:42:32,049
When I first met you.

963
00:42:33,518 --> 00:42:34,384
So...

964
00:42:34,653 --> 00:42:36,286
We hadn't talked back then.

965
00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:38,288
Just based on first impressions.

966
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:39,622
I see.

967
00:42:39,958 --> 00:42:40,791
So,

968
00:42:41,792 --> 00:42:43,360
you know,

969
00:42:43,562 --> 00:42:45,496
I always tell you you're so pretty.

970
00:42:45,497 --> 00:42:47,898
And I mean every word.

971
00:42:49,367 --> 00:42:51,201
You were different in that sense.

972
00:42:51,202 --> 00:42:52,002
Like...

973
00:42:52,271 --> 00:42:54,171
I was supposed to get to know you,

974
00:42:54,172 --> 00:42:56,272
but I was already into you.

975
00:42:56,975 --> 00:42:59,644
I should take my time to get to know you,
but I already liked you.

976
00:43:01,779 --> 00:43:03,379
So I didn't know...

977
00:43:04,448 --> 00:43:06,249
what to do with that feeling.

978
00:43:06,517 --> 00:43:09,452
- It was your first time?
- I've never felt this way before.

979
00:43:09,487 --> 00:43:10,387
(Thinking)

980
00:43:10,388 --> 00:43:11,555
He was caught off guard.

981
00:43:11,856 --> 00:43:13,291
Since I liked you so much,

982
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:19,562
I didn't know how to approach you
or talk to you.

983
00:43:19,897 --> 00:43:21,032
That's why I went all-in.

984
00:43:21,132 --> 00:43:23,868
He should be getting to know her,
but he already liked her.

985
00:43:24,102 --> 00:43:26,170
That means it was love at first sight.

986
00:43:26,671 --> 00:43:28,772
He's never felt that way before.

987
00:43:28,773 --> 00:43:30,340
He liked her so much...

988
00:43:30,341 --> 00:43:31,876
that he just had to pursue her.

989
00:43:34,512 --> 00:43:38,448
I also think it's hard to find someone
you really click with.

990
00:43:38,549 --> 00:43:43,588
Finding someone who likes you back
is such a blessing.

991
00:43:43,589 --> 00:43:44,421
Yes.

992
00:43:44,422 --> 00:43:47,724
So I really like you,

993
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:50,794
even though I'm not sure
about how you feel.

994
00:43:50,995 --> 00:43:52,396
But if you like me too...

995
00:43:53,031 --> 00:43:56,100
I think we hit it off pretty well too.

996
00:43:59,404 --> 00:44:01,234
It'd be nice if we dated.

997
00:44:01,606 --> 00:44:03,440
That's what I thought.

998
00:44:05,977 --> 00:44:07,544
Did I talk too much?

999
00:44:07,545 --> 00:44:09,447
I feel like you don't have
any questions for me.

1000
00:44:10,982 --> 00:44:12,115
Actually, I do,

1001
00:44:12,116 --> 00:44:13,850
but I don't want
to make you uncomfortable.

1002
00:44:14,219 --> 00:44:15,652
Ask away!

1003
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:18,421
Since there's a big age gap,

1004
00:44:18,790 --> 00:44:22,826
I might be asking questions
you haven't really thought about.

1005
00:44:23,394 --> 00:44:24,795
So I feel a little hesitant to ask.

1006
00:44:26,798 --> 00:44:29,433
I have a lot of questions,

1007
00:44:29,634 --> 00:44:32,737
but maybe you haven't thought
about these things at your age yet.

1008
00:44:33,371 --> 00:44:35,205
My questions are...

1009
00:44:36,474 --> 00:44:38,509
They might be about the future.

1010
00:44:41,045 --> 00:44:44,180
So I just hope
you have more questions for me.

1011
00:44:47,118 --> 00:44:50,087
But you seem hesitant to ask me things.

1012
00:44:50,455 --> 00:44:53,390
It feels like we're not really
getting deeper.

1013
00:44:55,760 --> 00:44:56,927
It's not easy.

1014
00:44:57,762 --> 00:44:59,763
It's a little hard...

1015
00:45:00,865 --> 00:45:01,898
- What?
- for me too.

1016
00:45:01,899 --> 00:45:02,699
Okay.

1017
00:45:04,135 --> 00:45:05,435
(Hesitating)

1018
00:45:05,770 --> 00:45:07,971
It seems like...

1019
00:45:09,507 --> 00:45:14,511
you're more focused
on getting married soon.

1020
00:45:15,146 --> 00:45:16,847
- Not really.
- You seem kind of rushed.

1021
00:45:18,449 --> 00:45:20,784
- You shouldn't have said that!
- Hey!

1022
00:45:21,086 --> 00:45:23,520
You were doing so well.
What are you doing?

1023
00:45:23,588 --> 00:45:26,089
- After "much older"?
- Hey, that's not right.

1024
00:45:26,090 --> 00:45:27,457
- What?
- "You seem rushed."

1025
00:45:27,458 --> 00:45:29,859
That wasn't the right thing to say.

1026
00:45:29,860 --> 00:45:31,294
He suddenly took a weird turn.

1027
00:45:31,295 --> 00:45:34,598
Yun So is so young
that he doesn't know how to word things.

1028
00:45:34,599 --> 00:45:37,000
He should've put it like,
"It seemed like..."

1029
00:45:37,001 --> 00:45:39,169
"getting married is more
of a priority for you."

1030
00:45:39,337 --> 00:45:41,838
- "You seem rushed."
- He isn't good with words.

1031
00:45:42,006 --> 00:45:44,007
Let's give him a break.

1032
00:45:44,609 --> 00:45:46,010
- Okay.
- Let this one slide.

1033
00:45:46,011 --> 00:45:47,144
This is his second slip-up.

1034
00:45:47,145 --> 00:45:48,079
Is that so?

1035
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:50,147
- He said she was much older.
- Right.

1036
00:45:51,149 --> 00:45:53,383
It seems like...

1037
00:45:54,852 --> 00:45:59,889
you're more focused
on getting married soon.

1038
00:46:00,491 --> 00:46:02,859
- Not really.
- You seem kind of rushed.

1039
00:46:02,860 --> 00:46:03,760
Really?

1040
00:46:03,962 --> 00:46:05,628
I'm not rushed.

1041
00:46:07,465 --> 00:46:11,268
I want to date someone I could marry.

1042
00:46:11,669 --> 00:46:15,939
I'm more focused on dating,

1043
00:46:16,274 --> 00:46:17,207
but...

1044
00:46:17,576 --> 00:46:21,678
I thought you seemed more focused
on getting married.

1045
00:46:21,679 --> 00:46:22,714
Well, I am,

1046
00:46:22,715 --> 00:46:23,848
but it's half and half.

1047
00:46:24,248 --> 00:46:26,783
To be honest,

1048
00:46:28,186 --> 00:46:33,023
I'm not in the same situation as you.

1049
00:46:33,191 --> 00:46:34,091
So...

1050
00:46:35,026 --> 00:46:37,361
when I date someone,

1051
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:40,397
I take it more seriously than you do.

1052
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:45,068
Having a happy family is...

1053
00:46:46,337 --> 00:46:48,705
one of my life goals,

1054
00:46:49,307 --> 00:46:53,109
but I've never really
thought deeply about it.

1055
00:46:53,611 --> 00:46:54,744
I kind of knew that,

1056
00:46:55,246 --> 00:46:56,913
so I was hesitant to ask you questions.

1057
00:46:56,914 --> 00:46:59,850
Right. That's why I'm scared
to ask you questions too.

1058
00:47:03,788 --> 00:47:06,624
I feel like no matter what I ask,

1059
00:47:06,891 --> 00:47:11,661
the conversation always ends up...

1060
00:47:12,164 --> 00:47:13,730
about marriage.

1061
00:47:13,864 --> 00:47:15,865
What? You don't know that.

1062
00:47:15,866 --> 00:47:19,302
- Depending on the question...
- It does depend on the question.

1063
00:47:19,303 --> 00:47:23,640
I don't think about marriage
every time you say something.

1064
00:47:24,108 --> 00:47:25,608
- Right.
- I didn't come on this show...

1065
00:47:25,609 --> 00:47:27,377
to get married.

1066
00:47:27,378 --> 00:47:29,212
- I came here to find someone to date.
- Right.

1067
00:47:29,647 --> 00:47:30,513
So...

1068
00:47:31,415 --> 00:47:34,917
I want to ask questions
that are more about you as a person.

1069
00:47:35,653 --> 00:47:37,454
That's what I try to do.

1070
00:47:39,657 --> 00:47:41,592
Then just focus on what you think.

1071
00:47:42,459 --> 00:47:45,295
Right now, you should focus on yourself.

1072
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,399
He seems to have a lot on his mind.

1073
00:47:54,272 --> 00:47:59,009
(Their last date ended with them
talking past each other.)

1074
00:47:59,844 --> 00:48:02,512
That conversation will affect...

1075
00:48:02,513 --> 00:48:04,080
the two of them a lot.

1076
00:48:05,216 --> 00:48:06,783
If they were to have a conflict,

1077
00:48:06,784 --> 00:48:07,884
- Right.
- it would be about that.

1078
00:48:07,885 --> 00:48:09,319
It's something...

1079
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:11,654
they'll eventually have to face
and talk about.

1080
00:48:12,623 --> 00:48:13,490
(Yeon House)

1081
00:48:13,491 --> 00:48:17,427
(Meanwhile, at Yeon House,)

1082
00:48:18,095 --> 00:48:22,131
(Jin Woo asked Jin Young to talk
as she came back early from her date.)

1083
00:48:22,934 --> 00:48:24,335
The weather is so nice today.

1084
00:48:25,102 --> 00:48:27,570
- I know.
- Lying down alone,

1085
00:48:28,405 --> 00:48:31,308
I wondered why this happened to me
on such a nice day.

1086
00:48:31,709 --> 00:48:34,177
I'm pretty sure
the guys will get to choose tomorrow.

1087
00:48:34,178 --> 00:48:35,379
Then do you want...

1088
00:48:37,082 --> 00:48:38,682
What were you going to say?

1089
00:48:38,683 --> 00:48:40,083
What was it?

1090
00:48:40,151 --> 00:48:41,084
Just...

1091
00:48:41,752 --> 00:48:44,021
I thought about a scenario
you wouldn't want.

1092
00:48:44,355 --> 00:48:46,656
Where Jung Won didn't choose you,

1093
00:48:46,657 --> 00:48:47,992
so we end up on a date.

1094
00:48:48,559 --> 00:48:50,426
That's not the ideal situation for you.

1095
00:48:53,064 --> 00:48:53,964
Right?

1096
00:48:53,965 --> 00:48:56,200
Well, I have fun hanging out with you.

1097
00:48:56,700 --> 00:48:58,335
You shouldn't just enjoy
hanging out with me.

1098
00:48:58,336 --> 00:48:59,904
You should want to date me.

1099
00:49:01,906 --> 00:49:03,389
You're sure about how you feel, right?

1100
00:49:05,376 --> 00:49:06,776
Yes.

1101
00:49:07,111 --> 00:49:08,846
You get jealous easily, right?

1102
00:49:08,946 --> 00:49:10,114
- Jealous?
- Yes.

1103
00:49:10,581 --> 00:49:13,883
You seem like the type
who falls hard when you like someone.

1104
00:49:13,884 --> 00:49:16,052
- From the start?
- Like I'm flooring it?

1105
00:49:16,354 --> 00:49:17,421
Yes.

1106
00:49:17,581 --> 00:49:20,183
You don't seem like the type
who develops feelings slowly.

1107
00:49:20,357 --> 00:49:22,792
You go from 0 to 90 real quick.

1108
00:49:23,527 --> 00:49:25,094
Did I come across that way?

1109
00:49:25,463 --> 00:49:26,329
Yes.

1110
00:49:26,997 --> 00:49:30,366
- I'm a little caught off guard.
- I like that you're honest.

1111
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:31,734
I can explain.

1112
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:34,604
When we talked the day before,

1113
00:49:34,705 --> 00:49:37,440
you could've just listened
and given me a simple response.

1114
00:49:37,742 --> 00:49:39,276
But I felt like...

1115
00:49:39,277 --> 00:49:42,379
you were even more mature than I thought.

1116
00:49:42,879 --> 00:49:44,380
So the next day,

1117
00:49:44,949 --> 00:49:46,417
I wanted to talk to you more,

1118
00:49:46,442 --> 00:49:48,661
but I didn't expect
to go on a date with you.

1119
00:49:48,686 --> 00:49:50,321
Even though it wasn't a 1-on-1.

1120
00:49:50,588 --> 00:49:54,890
I enjoyed spending time with you
in a romantic way.

1121
00:49:54,891 --> 00:49:57,828
I didn't just have fun as friends.

1122
00:49:59,607 --> 00:50:04,739
That's why I acted that way
while we were dating.

1123
00:50:05,833 --> 00:50:08,739
Even when we talked late last night
after we got back to the house,

1124
00:50:10,066 --> 00:50:12,599
you listened to me so well.

1125
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:14,512
How could I not start seeing you that way?

1126
00:50:14,933 --> 00:50:16,399
I don't know.

1127
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:18,883
I'm not really sure what you mean
by "listened to you so well."

1128
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:22,686
You're the first person I've had
a truly deep conversation with here.

1129
00:50:23,533 --> 00:50:25,422
No one here knows anything about my life.

1130
00:50:25,933 --> 00:50:29,232
But you made me feel comfortable enough
to open up to you.

1131
00:50:29,233 --> 00:50:30,995
That's why everything
came out so naturally.

1132
00:50:33,300 --> 00:50:34,932
That's why there's a reason
for my feelings.

1133
00:50:34,933 --> 00:50:36,967
I didn't suddenly start coming on
to you for no reason.

1134
00:50:37,266 --> 00:50:41,499
It wasn't some shallow,
black-and-white reaction where I thought,

1135
00:50:41,500 --> 00:50:43,741
"She's nice to me,
so maybe I'll show interest too."

1136
00:50:44,966 --> 00:50:46,999
He's saying his feelings didn't
just come out of nowhere.

1137
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:48,299
He's saying there's a story behind them.

1138
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:49,832
That there's a reason for them.

1139
00:50:49,833 --> 00:50:55,533
For now, I want to talk to Jung Won
one more time today...

1140
00:50:57,200 --> 00:50:59,800
if he's okay with it.

1141
00:51:03,333 --> 00:51:04,432
That's really heartbreaking.

1142
00:51:04,433 --> 00:51:07,899
If you get a chance to make your decision,

1143
00:51:07,900 --> 00:51:09,300
whether it's tomorrow or the day after,

1144
00:51:10,933 --> 00:51:13,700
I hope you won't rule me out.

1145
00:51:17,900 --> 00:51:18,966
That's all I'm asking.

1146
00:51:19,300 --> 00:51:20,266
Okay.

1147
00:51:22,233 --> 00:51:24,199
He's really trying to keep
the conversation going.

1148
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:30,633
(Can Jin Woo's sincere feelings
reach Jin Young?)

1149
00:51:30,900 --> 00:51:34,465
Jin Young struggles to keep
a conversation going with Jung Won,

1150
00:51:34,466 --> 00:51:36,832
but somehow she never runs out
of things to say with Jin Woo.

1151
00:51:36,833 --> 00:51:41,299
And I think Jin Woo is really good
at drawing that out.

1152
00:51:41,300 --> 00:51:44,268
That's because she doesn't feel pressured
when she's with Jin Woo,

1153
00:51:44,566 --> 00:51:46,537
so the conversation flows more naturally.

1154
00:51:48,300 --> 00:51:53,200
(Meanwhile, Ji Seung returns
after her date with Si Won.)

1155
00:51:53,633 --> 00:51:54,866
- See you later.
- See you.

1156
00:51:55,333 --> 00:51:57,766
Everyone's heading back to the house.

1157
00:52:01,933 --> 00:52:03,799
(Sighing)

1158
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:05,233
Oh, Ju Hee...

1159
00:52:09,300 --> 00:52:13,133
(Ju Hee walks in with a deep sigh.)

1160
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:17,299
Let me take a short break.

1161
00:52:17,300 --> 00:52:18,602
She definitely needs it.

1162
00:52:18,866 --> 00:52:19,766
Just a short one.

1163
00:52:21,833 --> 00:52:24,132
(She looks exhausted.)

1164
00:52:24,133 --> 00:52:25,500
It was an exhausting date.

1165
00:52:27,839 --> 00:52:30,222
That must've been a date
that gave her a lot to think about.

1166
00:52:30,600 --> 00:52:32,265
(Meanwhile, in the common area)

1167
00:52:32,266 --> 00:52:33,866
Things feel a little tense.

1168
00:52:34,466 --> 00:52:36,133
Aren't the others back yet?

1169
00:52:37,266 --> 00:52:40,466
(Jung Won and Ji Hye
still haven't returned.)

1170
00:52:40,733 --> 00:52:43,333
Why are they taking so long?

1171
00:52:43,600 --> 00:52:45,032
She must be really upset.

1172
00:52:45,033 --> 00:52:46,033
Seriously.

1173
00:52:47,066 --> 00:52:48,599
Why are they taking so long?

1174
00:52:48,833 --> 00:52:52,100
It's written all over your face.
You're really worried.

1175
00:52:52,833 --> 00:52:54,099
Of course, she's heartbroken.

1176
00:52:54,100 --> 00:52:56,674
The guy she likes is out
with someone else,

1177
00:52:56,698 --> 00:52:57,809
and they're still not back.

1178
00:52:57,833 --> 00:53:01,866
(Jin Woo can't help but notice Jin Young.)

1179
00:53:02,566 --> 00:53:03,765
They're all back.

1180
00:53:03,766 --> 00:53:04,765
- All of them?
- Yes.

1181
00:53:04,766 --> 00:53:06,666
(Just then, Jung Won and Ji Hye arrive.)

1182
00:53:08,333 --> 00:53:10,800
They even look like they're
wearing matching outfits.

1183
00:53:12,100 --> 00:53:15,832
- Hello.
- Welcome back.

1184
00:53:15,833 --> 00:53:17,166
Hi.

1185
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:20,130
Jung Won looks so happy.

1186
00:53:20,533 --> 00:53:21,600
I don't.

1187
00:53:22,233 --> 00:53:23,465
You really do.

1188
00:53:23,466 --> 00:53:24,765
- Not at all.
- You look delighted.

1189
00:53:24,766 --> 00:53:26,603
(Ji Hye looks bright as well.)

1190
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:30,233
(Looking away)

1191
00:53:30,633 --> 00:53:31,699
Oh, no.

1192
00:53:31,700 --> 00:53:33,099
I had three bowls of rice.

1193
00:53:33,124 --> 00:53:34,724
- Three bowls?
- Yes.

1194
00:53:35,100 --> 00:53:36,980
Can't you read the room a little?

1195
00:53:37,933 --> 00:53:40,400
He goes straight over
and sits next to Ji Hye,

1196
00:53:41,733 --> 00:53:43,887
while Jin Young is all the way at the end.

1197
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:46,156
What are you supposed to do
in a situation like that?

1198
00:53:49,800 --> 00:53:51,799
Jung Won, did you have dinner?

1199
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:53,432
We had dried pollock and egg soup.

1200
00:53:53,433 --> 00:53:55,033
- I'm so full.
- Really?

1201
00:53:55,733 --> 00:53:58,065
We also had rice balls
and spicy chicken feet.

1202
00:53:58,066 --> 00:54:00,033
Chicken feet? That must've been so good.

1203
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:03,832
We're not at the stage...

1204
00:54:03,833 --> 00:54:06,632
where we're too nervous to eat
when we're together anymore.

1205
00:54:06,633 --> 00:54:08,127
So I figured we should eat
as much as we could...

1206
00:54:08,152 --> 00:54:09,139
while we had the chance.

1207
00:54:09,700 --> 00:54:12,066
I'm completely stuffed now.

1208
00:54:14,050 --> 00:54:15,152
Open this for me.

1209
00:54:15,900 --> 00:54:18,099
Asking him to open the bottle
was on purpose, wasn't it?

1210
00:54:18,100 --> 00:54:19,032
Of course.

1211
00:54:19,033 --> 00:54:21,966
It might not have been conscious,
but it probably came out instinctively.

1212
00:54:23,786 --> 00:54:26,140
It took shorter than expected.

1213
00:54:26,164 --> 00:54:27,063
Forty minutes?

1214
00:54:27,300 --> 00:54:30,866
(They look a lot closer after the date.)

1215
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:35,432
(Jin Young finally gets up
and walks away.)

1216
00:54:35,433 --> 00:54:36,633
Oh, dear.

1217
00:54:45,933 --> 00:54:48,432
I wouldn't be able to stay there either.

1218
00:54:48,433 --> 00:54:49,665
I'd probably end up crying.

1219
00:54:49,666 --> 00:54:50,888
I know. I'd be in tears too.

1220
00:54:54,166 --> 00:54:55,365
This is so heartbreaking.

1221
00:54:55,366 --> 00:54:57,132
My heart hurts just watching this.

1222
00:54:57,133 --> 00:55:01,065
Still, I don't think Jung Won should
go comfort Jin Young...

1223
00:55:01,066 --> 00:55:02,799
after coming back to the house.

1224
00:55:02,800 --> 00:55:04,499
That'd be the end of things with Ji Hye.

1225
00:55:04,500 --> 00:55:05,903
- He can't do that.
- I agree.

1226
00:55:06,800 --> 00:55:10,666
(Jin Young comes back to her room.)

1227
00:55:12,733 --> 00:55:13,965
Who is it?

1228
00:55:13,966 --> 00:55:14,899
It's me, Jin Young.

1229
00:55:14,900 --> 00:55:16,866
- What?
- It's good that Ju Hee is there.

1230
00:55:17,866 --> 00:55:18,765
What happened?

1231
00:55:18,766 --> 00:55:20,565
- What?
- What's going on?

1232
00:55:20,566 --> 00:55:23,399
If you keep talking to her,
she'll break down.

1233
00:55:23,400 --> 00:55:24,300
Are you okay?

1234
00:55:24,833 --> 00:55:26,356
I need some time to compose myself.

1235
00:55:27,666 --> 00:55:30,366
(Startled)

1236
00:55:32,033 --> 00:55:33,200
Don't cry.

1237
00:55:43,233 --> 00:55:46,166
Everything's been such a whirlwind,
hasn't it?

1238
00:55:48,433 --> 00:55:49,700
I'm okay.

1239
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:51,400
Geez.

1240
00:55:51,933 --> 00:55:53,877
She should let her emotions out here.

1241
00:55:56,333 --> 00:55:58,433
I think I'm the youngest one here.

1242
00:55:59,633 --> 00:56:01,792
I must be the worst
at controlling my emotions.

1243
00:56:03,100 --> 00:56:06,366
For now, I need to get myself together.

1244
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:09,966
I came here to compose myself...

1245
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:12,833
because I don't think I can keep
my expression under control...

1246
00:56:13,833 --> 00:56:17,333
while everyone is in the common area.

1247
00:56:18,533 --> 00:56:20,999
Then I'll step out. Calm down here.

1248
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:22,632
If I stay here, I think you'll cry.

1249
00:56:22,633 --> 00:56:24,648
- Just tell them I went to the bathroom.
- Okay.

1250
00:56:25,266 --> 00:56:26,733
- Take your time.
- Okay.

1251
00:56:34,133 --> 00:56:35,532
(The moment Ju Hee leaves,)

1252
00:56:35,533 --> 00:56:36,827
This is so heartbreaking.

1253
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:40,413
(Jin Young's emotions come rushing in.)

1254
00:56:43,133 --> 00:56:48,233
Don't show it. Never show it.

1255
00:56:48,966 --> 00:56:53,500
(Jin Young tries
to hold her emotions together.)

1256
00:56:59,900 --> 00:57:01,133
Don't show it.

1257
00:57:06,933 --> 00:57:07,733
Okay.

1258
00:57:09,100 --> 00:57:13,233
Why are you still so immature, Jin Young?

1259
00:57:18,166 --> 00:57:22,466
She's actually doing a great job
controlling herself.

1260
00:57:23,066 --> 00:57:25,665
She's really strong and mature.

1261
00:57:25,666 --> 00:57:28,100
Right. She's handling herself so well.

1262
00:57:29,633 --> 00:57:32,766
(Jin Young comes back with Ji Seung.)

1263
00:57:33,366 --> 00:57:36,132
(She cannot bring herself to look
toward Jung Won and Ji Hye.)

1264
00:57:36,133 --> 00:57:38,133
This is so hard to watch.

1265
00:57:42,366 --> 00:57:44,232
(The last couple arrives at the house.)

1266
00:57:44,233 --> 00:57:45,800
They're coming.

1267
00:57:46,733 --> 00:57:48,132
- Everyone is here.
- They're all back.

1268
00:57:48,133 --> 00:57:49,699
(Si Won and Yu Jin head straight
to the common area.)

1269
00:57:49,700 --> 00:57:51,332
- You're back.
- Welcome back.

1270
00:57:51,333 --> 00:57:52,633
Hi.

1271
00:57:53,433 --> 00:57:55,033
What's wrong with Si Won?

1272
00:57:55,400 --> 00:57:56,699
In the car...

1273
00:57:56,700 --> 00:58:00,200
Why are Si Won's eyes so unfocused?
What's wrong with him?

1274
00:58:00,600 --> 00:58:03,365
- Your eyes are completely out of it.
- He's totally out of it.

1275
00:58:03,366 --> 00:58:04,165
His hair is messy too.

1276
00:58:04,166 --> 00:58:07,733
Why is the back of your hair
all messed up?

1277
00:58:08,166 --> 00:58:10,199
- Oh, really?
- What happened?

1278
00:58:10,200 --> 00:58:13,633
We were so tired that we slept
the entire way back in the car.

1279
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:16,699
We went to a caravan today...

1280
00:58:16,700 --> 00:58:18,666
- Really?
- and had a barbecue there.

1281
00:58:21,300 --> 00:58:25,166
(Jung Won briefly leaves the area.)

1282
00:58:25,766 --> 00:58:28,332
- Can I go lie down for a bit?
- Go ahead.

1283
00:58:28,333 --> 00:58:30,832
I'm going to sleep in my room for a bit.
Can you wake me up later?

1284
00:58:30,833 --> 00:58:34,966
(Ji Hye goes to her room
to get some rest.)

1285
00:58:37,000 --> 00:58:38,532
(As soon as Ji Hye leaves,
Jung Won comes back.)

1286
00:58:38,533 --> 00:58:39,783
The timing is unbelievable.

1287
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,799
- Jung Won, let's go outside.
- What?

1288
00:58:41,800 --> 00:58:43,265
- Let's talk for a bit.
- Okay.

1289
00:58:43,266 --> 00:58:44,133
Right now.

1290
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:49,300
You have no idea what will happen
the moment you leave the common area.

1291
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:51,428
This place is like a jungle.

1292
00:58:52,500 --> 00:58:54,265
It's not that cold.
Do you want to talk outside?

1293
00:58:54,266 --> 00:58:56,866
- Okay, let's talk outside.
- Good.

1294
00:58:57,866 --> 00:59:01,666
(Then Yun So leaves as well.)

1295
00:59:02,666 --> 00:59:04,032
(Only four people remain
in the common area.)

1296
00:59:04,033 --> 00:59:06,265
I think I slept really well in the car.

1297
00:59:06,266 --> 00:59:08,133
Is that Ji Seung sitting across from them?

1298
00:59:09,633 --> 00:59:10,566
I was...

1299
00:59:11,533 --> 00:59:13,432
really grateful
that Jin Woo took pictures of us.

1300
00:59:13,433 --> 00:59:15,965
Right. You took pictures of the two of us.

1301
00:59:15,966 --> 00:59:18,332
When I saw you,
you looked so good together.

1302
00:59:18,333 --> 00:59:19,389
So I started taking pictures.

1303
00:59:22,633 --> 00:59:24,565
I kept finding myself looking at them.

1304
00:59:24,566 --> 00:59:26,365
Don't you like that kind of vibe?
The colors and everything.

1305
00:59:26,366 --> 00:59:28,000
- They looked really natural.
- Right.

1306
00:59:28,566 --> 00:59:29,633
I'll be back.

1307
00:59:31,566 --> 00:59:34,233
(And then Yu Jin leaves as well.)

1308
00:59:34,533 --> 00:59:37,832
(Only the three of them remain
in the common area.)

1309
00:59:37,833 --> 00:59:39,233
(Yawning)

1310
00:59:39,500 --> 00:59:40,899
Shouldn't you go to sleep?

1311
00:59:40,900 --> 00:59:42,999
Right. I'm so sleepy.

1312
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:44,065
Are you tired, or are you sleepy?

1313
00:59:44,066 --> 00:59:45,666
- Is she drinking?
- Both, maybe.

1314
00:59:46,100 --> 00:59:47,199
Did you get to spend some quality time?

1315
00:59:47,200 --> 00:59:49,032
(They seem to be in completely
different spaces.)

1316
00:59:49,033 --> 00:59:51,365
- I did drink quite a lot today.
- Oh, no.

1317
00:59:51,366 --> 00:59:53,000
I don't know if I'll have enough energy.

1318
00:59:53,666 --> 00:59:56,300
Is it just you and me now?

1319
00:59:57,006 --> 01:00:01,017
Our timing kept missing by a fraction.

1320
01:00:01,331 --> 01:00:02,231
And...

1321
01:00:03,200 --> 01:00:06,635
there was a difference
in how we communicate things.

1322
01:00:06,636 --> 01:00:09,539
If I had chosen Si Won at that time,

1323
01:00:09,540 --> 01:00:12,608
I could have given him assurance...

1324
01:00:12,977 --> 01:00:15,145
about how he chose me in the beginning.

1325
01:00:15,146 --> 01:00:17,648
I think that was an important opportunity.

1326
01:00:17,649 --> 01:00:19,315
Which I missed.

1327
01:00:20,784 --> 01:00:23,119
Not only about my relationship
with Si Won,

1328
01:00:23,120 --> 01:00:25,187
but I was also upset about everything.

1329
01:00:25,856 --> 01:00:29,225
It's true that I'm the one
who chose to come here.

1330
01:00:29,692 --> 01:00:32,428
But it was really hard
for me to make choices every day.

1331
01:00:32,729 --> 01:00:34,596
It was really challenging,

1332
01:00:35,499 --> 01:00:39,302
and I tried to make decisions
by my own standards.

1333
01:00:43,473 --> 01:00:44,873
- She's getting emotional.
- It could be sad.

1334
01:00:44,874 --> 01:00:46,141
- It is hard.
- It is.

1335
01:00:46,142 --> 01:00:50,245
(Ji Seung having many mixed emotions)

1336
01:00:50,315 --> 01:00:51,881
For the rest,

1337
01:00:52,149 --> 01:00:53,683
I'll have to leave it to him.

1338
01:00:53,684 --> 01:00:56,586
There are other people.

1339
01:00:57,020 --> 01:00:59,688
There is Yu Jin as well.

1340
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:02,592
But it's like this.

1341
01:01:02,593 --> 01:01:06,428
There is the pace of dating programs,
and then there's her own pace.

1342
01:01:06,429 --> 01:01:08,278
The discrepancy
between that can't be helped.

1343
01:01:08,279 --> 01:01:09,799
- Right.
- When you're on a show...

1344
01:01:09,800 --> 01:01:12,067
She's never had to do these things before.

1345
01:01:12,068 --> 01:01:13,502
And she won't in the future either.

1346
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:15,904
Her pace didn't work
for the dating show...

1347
01:01:15,905 --> 01:01:17,740
but she did the best she could.

1348
01:01:17,741 --> 01:01:18,741
Of course.

1349
01:01:19,200 --> 01:01:22,411
(Jin Young and Jung Won are sitting
across each other.)

1350
01:01:23,113 --> 01:01:24,613
(Awkward air between them)

1351
01:01:24,614 --> 01:01:26,148
That is a very scary air between them.

1352
01:01:29,453 --> 01:01:32,321
I actually wanted to tell you...

1353
01:01:32,756 --> 01:01:34,090
as soon as possible.

1354
01:01:35,258 --> 01:01:36,291
Is he finally telling her?

1355
01:01:36,292 --> 01:01:38,827
Until today,

1356
01:01:38,828 --> 01:01:41,930
I've talked to both you and Ji Hye a lot.

1357
01:01:42,599 --> 01:01:43,432
He's telling her.

1358
01:01:44,534 --> 01:01:45,567
Finally.

1359
01:01:46,203 --> 01:01:49,772
But when I talked to Ji Hye today,

1360
01:01:51,842 --> 01:01:54,610
I had a change of heart.

1361
01:01:55,612 --> 01:01:56,612
And I wavered a bit.

1362
01:02:01,885 --> 01:02:03,051
You and I...

1363
01:02:03,052 --> 01:02:07,089
I always felt there was a strange line
between us.

1364
01:02:09,393 --> 01:02:11,727
I've also felt that.

1365
01:02:12,063 --> 01:02:17,133
Obviously, at first,
there was a certain emotional...

1366
01:02:19,136 --> 01:02:21,203
- tension between us.
- Yes.

1367
01:02:21,204 --> 01:02:23,439
But even on our date today,

1368
01:02:23,440 --> 01:02:24,574
(She also felt the same way.)

1369
01:02:24,575 --> 01:02:26,075
I felt pretty uncomfortable.

1370
01:02:26,076 --> 01:02:27,844
- Yes. I agree.
- I didn't feel comfortable.

1371
01:02:27,845 --> 01:02:28,678
Same.

1372
01:02:29,446 --> 01:02:32,114
- It's actually nice talking to you.
- Yeah.

1373
01:02:32,316 --> 01:02:34,517
I love to talk about work with you.

1374
01:02:34,518 --> 01:02:36,585
- I love such conversations.
- I know.

1375
01:02:36,987 --> 01:02:39,588
When I'm with you,

1376
01:02:40,490 --> 01:02:42,624
I end up having productive conversations.

1377
01:02:43,860 --> 01:02:45,995
- Kind of like...
- I think I understand.

1378
01:02:45,996 --> 01:02:48,931
- conversations before talking marriage.
- Right.

1379
01:02:49,032 --> 01:02:51,367
So when I think about that...

1380
01:02:52,736 --> 01:02:54,870
if we hadn't talked about it at all...

1381
01:02:54,871 --> 01:02:56,506
(Maybe they were lacking comfortable,
everyday conversations.)

1382
01:02:56,507 --> 01:02:59,141
We've talked about so many things...

1383
01:02:59,142 --> 01:03:00,843
about our business.

1384
01:03:01,411 --> 01:03:04,513
But when I talk to Ji Hye...

1385
01:03:04,881 --> 01:03:06,148
there wasn't that line between us.

1386
01:03:07,985 --> 01:03:11,454
And I think that worked positively for me.

1387
01:03:12,722 --> 01:03:15,457
So I started thinking whether...

1388
01:03:16,493 --> 01:03:18,861
I should be waiting until tomorrow.

1389
01:03:20,064 --> 01:03:22,331
But I felt like
I shouldn't do that to you.

1390
01:03:22,432 --> 01:03:24,833
- He's finally putting it out there.
- Sure.

1391
01:03:24,834 --> 01:03:28,337
I think I can completely understand
what you're saying.

1392
01:03:28,338 --> 01:03:29,171
Okay.

1393
01:03:29,706 --> 01:03:31,841
There's only one thing I want to know.

1394
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:36,245
Is there any chance for me?

1395
01:03:36,246 --> 01:03:37,579
Or are you set on Ji Hye now?

1396
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:43,985
I think it's only right to tell you
as quickly as possible.

1397
01:03:44,821 --> 01:03:47,356
There isn't much time left now.

1398
01:03:47,357 --> 01:03:49,991
There's a deadline here.

1399
01:03:50,258 --> 01:03:52,758
It's final decisions tomorrow.

1400
01:03:52,759 --> 01:03:54,062
(She learns he's feelings
the day before final decisions.)

1401
01:03:54,063 --> 01:03:55,464
In this situation,

1402
01:03:55,699 --> 01:03:59,468
if I weigh things out and don't decide
until the very end...

1403
01:03:59,603 --> 01:04:01,504
I'll only be hurting you.

1404
01:04:03,173 --> 01:04:04,540
Yes. I respect that.

1405
01:04:05,375 --> 01:04:06,375
(Jin Young forcing a smile)

1406
01:04:06,376 --> 01:04:08,477
I respect it. It's okay.

1407
01:04:09,679 --> 01:04:11,647
I misjudged the situation as well.

1408
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:14,516
Maybe we should've only had
fun conversations.

1409
01:04:14,784 --> 01:04:16,385
That's not anybody's fault.

1410
01:04:16,386 --> 01:04:17,352
No.

1411
01:04:17,387 --> 01:04:19,189
Do we have to keep talking out here?

1412
01:04:19,190 --> 01:04:20,490
Do you want to go inside?

1413
01:04:20,491 --> 01:04:21,691
Sorry, I'm...

1414
01:04:21,692 --> 01:04:23,359
Do you feel uncomfortable here?

1415
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,126
I do.

1416
01:04:24,327 --> 01:04:26,528
I don't want to care too much.

1417
01:04:26,529 --> 01:04:28,775
(Jin Young's feelings linger
to end the conversation here.)

1418
01:04:31,201 --> 01:04:32,134
Cheers.

1419
01:04:32,135 --> 01:04:33,636
(They moved elsewhere to keep talking.)

1420
01:04:34,004 --> 01:04:37,473
This could be our last time
drinking together.

1421
01:04:42,512 --> 01:04:45,514
You can leave if you want.

1422
01:04:46,549 --> 01:04:47,415
You can leave.

1423
01:04:47,884 --> 01:04:49,050
You want to be alone?

1424
01:04:49,051 --> 01:04:49,852
Don't leave.

1425
01:04:53,356 --> 01:04:54,423
Why are you depressed?

1426
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:56,391
- I'm not.
- You look depressed.

1427
01:04:56,559 --> 01:04:57,792
Why are you so blue?

1428
01:04:57,861 --> 01:04:59,295
I can't be smiling.

1429
01:04:59,296 --> 01:05:00,529
Smile. It's okay.

1430
01:05:00,530 --> 01:05:01,835
It's better to mock me.

1431
01:05:01,836 --> 01:05:04,334
- Why would I mock you?
- "You should've done better!"

1432
01:05:04,335 --> 01:05:06,602
No, mock me. That's better.

1433
01:05:06,603 --> 01:05:07,703
No, not at all.

1434
01:05:08,271 --> 01:05:10,205
This is upsetting.

1435
01:05:10,206 --> 01:05:12,608
This is frustrating.

1436
01:05:13,243 --> 01:05:13,976
Why?

1437
01:05:16,313 --> 01:05:18,281
I didn't ask you...

1438
01:05:18,715 --> 01:05:20,515
about Ji Hye in depth...

1439
01:05:20,516 --> 01:05:22,317
on purpose.

1440
01:05:22,485 --> 01:05:23,318
Okay.

1441
01:05:23,787 --> 01:05:25,721
I've been avoiding it today.

1442
01:05:26,222 --> 01:05:28,657
Because continuing to ask you...

1443
01:05:28,658 --> 01:05:31,359
would be too much pressure for you.

1444
01:05:31,360 --> 01:05:32,727
(Jin Young didn't want
to pressure Jung Won.)

1445
01:05:32,796 --> 01:05:34,696
Maybe I was arrogant.

1446
01:05:35,599 --> 01:05:39,001
Maybe things would've been different
if I'd known.

1447
01:05:39,336 --> 01:05:40,169
Oh, dear.

1448
01:05:41,504 --> 01:05:42,771
Well, Jin Young.

1449
01:05:44,374 --> 01:05:48,978
Within the deadline
that I set up for myself,

1450
01:05:49,579 --> 01:05:52,147
I think my mind is made up.

1451
01:05:56,086 --> 01:06:00,892
- You're feeling the flirting stage here.
- Kind of.

1452
01:06:00,893 --> 01:06:02,425
- Right?
- That's true.

1453
01:06:02,492 --> 01:06:03,425
That's interesting.

1454
01:06:04,127 --> 01:06:07,129
(Jung Won put his hand on Ji Hye's knee.)

1455
01:06:10,533 --> 01:06:11,600
Funny.

1456
01:06:12,736 --> 01:06:15,171
(Grab)

1457
01:06:16,139 --> 01:06:21,043
(Ji Hye naturally held Jung Won's hand.)

1458
01:06:21,044 --> 01:06:23,479
(Staring)

1459
01:06:23,580 --> 01:06:25,747
Is it clear to you now?

1460
01:06:27,183 --> 01:06:28,350
I think it's you for me.

1461
01:06:32,055 --> 01:06:33,022
If I...

1462
01:06:34,223 --> 01:06:38,393
give you some kind of mixed message...

1463
01:06:38,495 --> 01:06:39,829
I don't want to do that.

1464
01:06:42,365 --> 01:06:43,265
I'm sorry.

1465
01:06:47,937 --> 01:06:49,671
It's no time for that.

1466
01:06:49,672 --> 01:06:50,705
(Jung Won has made up his mind.)

1467
01:06:50,706 --> 01:06:51,806
Good job, Jung Won.

1468
01:06:52,910 --> 01:06:54,310
Zero chance, then?

1469
01:06:55,846 --> 01:06:57,947
I don't want to confuse you anymore.

1470
01:06:58,982 --> 01:07:00,115
That's how I feel.

1471
01:07:02,519 --> 01:07:06,088
Hmm...

1472
01:07:06,089 --> 01:07:06,922
Okay.

1473
01:07:08,258 --> 01:07:10,226
I didn't have any expectations.

1474
01:07:11,461 --> 01:07:14,596
It's been a long time
since I felt something for someone.

1475
01:07:14,597 --> 01:07:16,498
A very long time.

1476
01:07:17,368 --> 01:07:19,802
I thought I couldn't feel
that way anymore.

1477
01:07:21,271 --> 01:07:23,939
But my heart fluttered because of you.

1478
01:07:24,574 --> 01:07:25,774
So I'm really grateful.

1479
01:07:26,876 --> 01:07:30,712
I realize that I could
feel that way again...

1480
01:07:30,914 --> 01:07:32,281
is something to be grateful for.

1481
01:07:34,784 --> 01:07:37,619
I just wanted to do my best...

1482
01:07:38,822 --> 01:07:40,122
to the end.

1483
01:07:41,991 --> 01:07:42,924
Thank you.

1484
01:07:44,828 --> 01:07:45,694
Really.

1485
01:07:45,695 --> 01:07:49,130
Jung Won left quite
an impact on Jin Young.

1486
01:07:50,266 --> 01:07:53,468
(She offering a handshake with a smile.)

1487
01:07:53,970 --> 01:07:54,803
Last handshake?

1488
01:08:00,810 --> 01:08:01,676
Let's go.

1489
01:08:02,879 --> 01:08:05,082
Well. I got rejected.

1490
01:08:05,682 --> 01:08:07,115
- No.
- One rejection so far.

1491
01:08:09,519 --> 01:08:10,619
It hurts a bit.

1492
01:08:10,620 --> 01:08:11,687
(They finished their last conversation.)

1493
01:08:11,688 --> 01:08:12,554
Oh, dear.

1494
01:08:14,557 --> 01:08:15,524
Good night.

1495
01:08:15,625 --> 01:08:16,658
- What about you?
- Go inside.

1496
01:08:20,630 --> 01:08:21,630
Come inside later.

1497
01:08:33,242 --> 01:08:38,880
(Jin Young wanders aimlessly.)

1498
01:08:45,221 --> 01:08:47,889
After Jung Won and Ji Hye
went on a date...

1499
01:08:48,524 --> 01:08:52,627
I expected him to make his decision...

1500
01:08:52,628 --> 01:08:55,864
after one more conversation with me.

1501
01:08:56,733 --> 01:09:01,437
And I thought even after going
on a date with Ji Hye...

1502
01:09:01,438 --> 01:09:04,073
he'd still choose me.

1503
01:09:04,074 --> 01:09:06,141
(I thought he'd choose me.)

1504
01:09:06,542 --> 01:09:10,478
But as soon as he came back
from his date with Ji Hye...

1505
01:09:10,479 --> 01:09:13,882
they were sitting together and talking...

1506
01:09:13,883 --> 01:09:15,750
like they were a couple already.

1507
01:09:16,486 --> 01:09:17,386
I was...

1508
01:09:17,921 --> 01:09:19,955
really flustered by that.

1509
01:09:21,057 --> 01:09:24,926
So I asked him to talk with me in private.

1510
01:09:27,697 --> 01:09:29,865
He had already made up his mind.

1511
01:09:30,334 --> 01:09:33,368
There was no chance for me...

1512
01:09:35,171 --> 01:09:36,871
to change his mind.

1513
01:09:38,908 --> 01:09:40,342
I don't want to cry.

1514
01:09:40,343 --> 01:09:41,943
I feel like I'm going to.

1515
01:09:46,416 --> 01:09:47,416
Excuse me.

1516
01:09:48,117 --> 01:09:49,785
Seriously.

1517
01:09:49,786 --> 01:09:52,520
I can't help but cry
when I talk about this.

1518
01:09:54,157 --> 01:09:56,424
I got too emotional yesterday.

1519
01:09:56,425 --> 01:09:58,494
I'm a lot better now.

1520
01:10:04,733 --> 01:10:06,833
Jung Won was already certain.

1521
01:10:07,100 --> 01:10:08,900
And there was no time left for me.

1522
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:16,532
I guess that was it.

1523
01:10:16,533 --> 01:10:19,832
I don't think there was
anything I could do.

1524
01:10:19,833 --> 01:10:22,266
(The night before the Final Selection,
with nothing but regrets left behind)

1525
01:10:23,300 --> 01:10:28,766
(Jin Young walked for a while afterward.)

1526
01:10:31,433 --> 01:10:33,966
(Clack)

1527
01:10:35,566 --> 01:10:36,366
Jin Young.

1528
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:38,300
Do you want to talk?

1529
01:10:38,933 --> 01:10:40,900
No way. It's so intense.

1530
01:10:41,266 --> 01:10:42,965
This is too much!

1531
01:10:42,966 --> 01:10:43,899
Seriously.

1532
01:10:43,900 --> 01:10:45,233
(How can it be?)

1533
01:10:45,566 --> 01:10:49,599
- I'm kind of losing it right now...
- I get it.

1534
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:51,633
I need to let this out.

1535
01:10:52,300 --> 01:10:54,200
Tomorrow, I have to...

1536
01:10:57,133 --> 01:10:59,665
You have bad taste in men.

1537
01:10:59,666 --> 01:11:00,533
Whatever.

1538
01:11:00,800 --> 01:11:03,200
- You really don't have a clue.
- No, I don't!

1539
01:11:04,700 --> 01:11:06,865
(Sighing)

1540
01:11:06,866 --> 01:11:08,633
Tell me. What did you talk about?

1541
01:11:09,433 --> 01:11:11,433
- With Jung Won?
- Yes. Tell me.

1542
01:11:13,933 --> 01:11:16,432
I honestly thought I had a shot.

1543
01:11:16,433 --> 01:11:18,265
- With Jung Won?
- Yes.

1544
01:11:18,266 --> 01:11:21,366
I thought by talking today...

1545
01:11:21,900 --> 01:11:24,366
- You thought you'd win him back.
- Right.

1546
01:11:24,933 --> 01:11:27,465
When I checked the QR yesterday,

1547
01:11:27,466 --> 01:11:30,133
it had been me
since the truth or dare game.

1548
01:11:30,466 --> 01:11:34,499
He led me on so much,
even until last night.

1549
01:11:34,500 --> 01:11:35,799
What did you do last night?

1550
01:11:35,800 --> 01:11:38,700
We held hands,
and I had my arms around his too.

1551
01:11:39,533 --> 01:11:42,700
So for me, all of that was...

1552
01:11:43,266 --> 01:11:45,199
A sign of certainty.

1553
01:11:45,200 --> 01:11:46,432
Yeah, totally.

1554
01:11:46,433 --> 01:11:48,899
I thought he was all-in for me.

1555
01:11:48,900 --> 01:11:49,865
She's got a point.

1556
01:11:49,866 --> 01:11:52,332
But after their date today,

1557
01:11:52,333 --> 01:11:55,532
they showed up practically as a couple.

1558
01:11:55,533 --> 01:11:56,333
Right.

1559
01:11:56,633 --> 01:11:58,133
But I...

1560
01:12:00,366 --> 01:12:03,133
To me, those two weren't...

1561
01:12:06,200 --> 01:12:08,399
(Jin Woo moves right next to Jin Young.)

1562
01:12:08,400 --> 01:12:10,033
He's trying to comfort her.

1563
01:12:11,200 --> 01:12:12,832
Do you mind if I cry?

1564
01:12:12,833 --> 01:12:14,300
Like a total loser?

1565
01:12:15,700 --> 01:12:20,533
(Her tears start pouring out
in front of Jin Woo.)

1566
01:12:23,433 --> 01:12:26,566
I wish you didn't waste your emotions
on things like this.

1567
01:12:26,866 --> 01:12:27,732
It's okay.

1568
01:12:27,733 --> 01:12:29,832
Why do you even like someone
who is making you cry?

1569
01:12:29,833 --> 01:12:31,399
I'm fine.

1570
01:12:31,400 --> 01:12:32,832
This is just how I feel.

1571
01:12:32,833 --> 01:12:35,032
It's not about what he did to me.

1572
01:12:35,033 --> 01:12:36,599
I know it's not about that,

1573
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:37,599
but you're crying now.

1574
01:12:37,600 --> 01:12:39,866
Why do you like someone who makes you cry?

1575
01:12:41,033 --> 01:12:43,233
I'm fine. Really.

1576
01:12:46,287 --> 01:12:50,999
I think it's funny that I came running
to you right after I got dumped.

1577
01:12:51,000 --> 01:12:51,900
I love it.

1578
01:12:52,433 --> 01:12:53,466
Just use me.

1579
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:57,199
Use me to vent out your anger.

1580
01:12:57,200 --> 01:12:59,600
Or just go on a date with me
tomorrow for them to see.

1581
01:13:00,300 --> 01:13:01,865
You don't even have to see me again,

1582
01:13:01,866 --> 01:13:03,666
so just go on a date with me tomorrow.
Please.

1583
01:13:05,600 --> 01:13:07,533
Why are you so nice to me?

1584
01:13:08,733 --> 01:13:12,532
I just don't understand why you're not
even trying to see me as a man.

1585
01:13:12,533 --> 01:13:14,500
To be honest, I can kind of see...

1586
01:13:14,932 --> 01:13:17,166
myself in you right now.

1587
01:13:19,200 --> 01:13:20,100
I just...

1588
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:23,466
want to be there for you.

1589
01:13:26,200 --> 01:13:28,000
I don't know if it's
because you're relatable,

1590
01:13:28,733 --> 01:13:30,799
or because I'm liking you more...

1591
01:13:30,800 --> 01:13:33,066
(Jin Woo confesses feelings that had
grown without him even realizing it.)

1592
01:13:33,733 --> 01:13:35,199
I just want you to spend a day with me...

1593
01:13:35,200 --> 01:13:36,432
and feel how much I mean it...

1594
01:13:36,433 --> 01:13:40,100
and realize how sincere I am.

1595
01:13:41,066 --> 01:13:45,599
(Jin Woo opens up one more time
about how he truly feels.)

1596
01:13:45,600 --> 01:13:47,205
I don't want to use you...

1597
01:13:47,206 --> 01:13:50,833
just because I'm going through
a hard time.

1598
01:13:52,333 --> 01:13:53,533
I don't mind it.

1599
01:13:54,833 --> 01:13:58,432
I don't want to give you false hope...

1600
01:13:58,433 --> 01:14:00,532
Right. How can she focus on a date...

1601
01:14:00,533 --> 01:14:02,199
when she's feeling like that?

1602
01:14:02,200 --> 01:14:03,800
It's not the end of the world for you.

1603
01:14:04,433 --> 01:14:05,332
Yeah.

1604
01:14:05,333 --> 01:14:08,033
I just hate
that you're wasting your tears.

1605
01:14:08,433 --> 01:14:10,866
It's just tears.

1606
01:14:11,433 --> 01:14:13,100
- It won't affect anything.
- Are you good now?

1607
01:14:13,433 --> 01:14:15,299
Has Jin Young put it behind her now?

1608
01:14:15,300 --> 01:14:17,633
- It's just meaningless tears.
- You're smiling.

1609
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:20,433
- Tears won't affect anything.
- I know, so don't cry.

1610
01:14:21,000 --> 01:14:24,733
(Will Jin Woo's confession
move Jin Young's heart?)

1611
01:14:25,066 --> 01:14:27,665
What can we do once we're out of here?

1612
01:14:27,666 --> 01:14:28,500
Just casual dating?

1613
01:14:28,933 --> 01:14:31,232
I don't think your feelings are
going to grow anymore,

1614
01:14:31,233 --> 01:14:35,132
and it feels like you don't want
a future with me.

1615
01:14:35,133 --> 01:14:37,166
It just feels like you don't have one.

1616
01:14:38,100 --> 01:14:39,700
I do have a job...

1617
01:14:40,800 --> 01:14:42,433
I just want you to have a bit of faith.

1618
01:14:43,333 --> 01:14:45,132
I'm not shallow.

1619
01:14:45,133 --> 01:14:46,433
But it feels like you think I am.

1620
01:14:47,966 --> 01:14:50,766
(Jin Young and Jin Woo's
final conversation)

1621
01:14:51,266 --> 01:14:53,733
I just really wanted to be there for you.

1622
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:56,266
I don't want you to cry.

1623
01:14:57,066 --> 01:14:58,700
If you're going to choose me,

1624
01:14:59,633 --> 01:15:02,433
I want it to be...

1625
01:15:03,533 --> 01:15:04,899
because you want me.

1626
01:15:04,900 --> 01:15:09,366
(Jin Woo tells Jin Young how he feels
for the last time.)

1627
01:15:09,666 --> 01:15:11,800
(The moment of the Final Selection has
finally arrived.)

1628
01:15:12,166 --> 01:15:14,333
I had a lot to think about.

1629
01:15:15,133 --> 01:15:18,200
I didn't think the differences
would simply disappear.

1630
01:15:18,966 --> 01:15:20,466
I have no regrets.

1631
01:15:21,466 --> 01:15:23,132
(They are finally facing
the Final Selection.)

1632
01:15:23,133 --> 01:15:26,633
(Did they feel the same way
about each other?)

1633
01:15:26,900 --> 01:15:29,665
(After the Final Selection at Yeon House,)

1634
01:15:29,666 --> 01:15:32,666
(they are given seven more days.)

1635
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:35,265
(They have left Yeon House...)

1636
01:15:35,266 --> 01:15:42,300
(and returned to their everyday lives.)

1637
01:15:42,866 --> 01:15:45,232
(Will they meet again
at the place they promised,)

1638
01:15:45,233 --> 01:15:48,900
(after seven days?)

1639
01:15:49,333 --> 01:15:50,133
What?

1640
01:15:50,933 --> 01:15:53,000
- Wait a minute.
- For real?

1641
01:15:54,066 --> 01:15:56,233
There's no way!

1642
01:15:56,234 --> 01:15:57,373
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
